<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="GAL" stage="Final" version="D">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="John Wimbish" created="2009-10-05 05:52:26Z" when="2009-10-05 05:52:26Z" stage="Draft">drafted by Lazarus Aplugi; keyboarded by Helena Aplugi; team revision 2007; with advisor Mar 2008; UNS in Ndao 26-27 Aug 08 w/Chuck &amp; team; Consultant Check in Kupang with Dave Glasgow, 10 Oct. 2008;</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Galati</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Sasuri Paulus<bt>Paulus' letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">hia juma'at-juma'at ètu propensi<bt>to the congregations in the province of</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Galati<bt>Galati</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii maho'o<bt>Greetings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1-2" />Lii maho'o nèti ja'a, Paulus. Ja'a pa'adhu sasuri ne asa a'ari aa'i-aa'i dhu parcaya Yesus Kristus ètu juma'at-juma'at ètu propensi Galati. A'ari dhu sama-sama dènge ja'a ètu ne'e, pa'adhu lii maho'o kahèi hia miu.<bt>Greetings from me, Paulus. I send this letter to all the siblings who believe in Yesus Kristus in the congregations in Galatia province. The siblings who are together with me here, also are sending greetings to you-pl.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ja'a pasanèd'e miu, na, Ama Lamatua dènge Yesus Kristus ka dhu pua-paleha ja'a. Nèti boe dhèu rai-haha ne. Yesus Kristus èèna, nuka Dhèu dhu Ama Lamatua pua mai le. Kristus madhe, te ngaa Lamatua pamamuri hari Ne. Hèia Ra pua-paleha ja'a, ho laku peka-padhai Lii Lolo Be'a dènge dhèu-dhèu.<bt>I remind you that it was Father God and Yesus Kristus who commissioned me. It was not from humans. That Yesus Kristus, that's the Person whom God has already sent coming. Kristus died, but God2 made [him] live again. Then/so They are the ones who ordered me to go tell (doublet) people about this Good News.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Paul, an apostle, not from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Paul, an apostle, not from man, neither through man, but through Jesus Christ, and God the Father who raised him from the dead, and all the brothers who are with me, to the congregations in Galatia;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ja'a sabaj'a mi Ama èdhi, Ama Lamatua, aa Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. Ja'a manèngi ho Rèngu pad'elo d'ara hua iia Ra mi miu, sèna ka miu mamuri padame èci dènge èci.<bt>I pray to God our-inc Father, and Yesus Kristus our Head. I ask that They show Their goodness/kindness/grace/mercy to you-pl (*key term mercy) so.that you can live in (relational) peace. [NOTE to daughter translations: this should be the same phrasing you used in 5T's and James. E.g. 2 Thes 1:2]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xaris: favor, grace, gift eirene: well-being,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">xaris: favor, grace, gift eirene: well-being, welfare, health, peace<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ,</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Kristus madhe, sèna ka saku eele aa'i sasala èdhi aa pakaj'èu èdhi nèti bhabhelu-katub'a rai-haha ne. Aa'i-aa'i dhu Kristus ad'u-ue sèra, madhutu dad'èi Ama Lamatua.<bt>Kristus died to wipe away our-inc wrongs, and to free/separate us-inc from the evil that is in this world now. All of that that Kristus did, [is] according to Father God's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exairew: rescue, set free, deliver aiwn:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">exairew: rescue, set free, deliver aiwn: age, period of time<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: who gave himself for our sins, to deliver us from the present evil age, according to the will of God, our Father,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Nèti èèna ka, èdhi hud'i koa-kio Ne taruu! Dhu lèke kèna!<bt>That's why we must continually praise Him! That's true/appropriate!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doksa: glory, praise. LITERALLY: to whom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">doksa: glory, praise. LITERALLY: to whom is glory forever and ever, Amen.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus nasa, lula dhèu Galati pusi-pahae boe Lii Lolo Be'a dhu lèke<bt>Paulus is angry because the Galatia people don't care about the true gospel/good news</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Ja'a ke'a heka tao miu sa mia! Ama Lamatua hag'e nare le miu, lula Na neo ho miu me'a d'ara hua iia Na. Te ngaa tasamia ka miu malai titu kèna lami madhutu lii lolo leo<bt>Siblings! I can no longer understand you-pl (+frustration)! God has chosen you, because He wants you to know/understand His good liver. But why have you quickly gone and followed/obeyed a different story/news</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thaumazw: wonder, marvel, be amazed, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">thaumazw: wonder, marvel, be amazed, be surprised, be astonished metatithemi: change, be removed, desert, turn away from, transfer<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: I am amazed that you so quickly are changing from the one who called you into the grace of Christ to another "good news,"</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />dhu lèke boe? Uuru èèna, ja'a aj'a le dhu mola-mola Lii Lolo Be'a nèti Yesus Kristus. Te ngaa limuri ne, dhèu kapod'e-kabèli sèra mai pakapod'e Lii Lolo Be'a èèna, toke miu malaa-maloha.<bt>that is not true? Previously, I had taught that which is true about Yesus Kristus' Good News. But now habitual decievers have come and twisted that Good News, to.the.point.of making you confused.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tarassw: stir up, disturb, unsettle, trouble,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">tarassw: stir up, disturb, unsettle, trouble, upset, confuse metastrephw: change, alter, pervert<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: which is not another [good news]. But there are some who are stirring you up, and want to pervert the Good News of Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Sanèd'e, ee! Te bèli-camèd'a Lamatua huku dhèu dhu aj'a Lii Lolo Be'a dhu sama boe dènge dhu ji'i aj'a-nori uru èèna. Masi ka dhèu nèti ji'i do, ana pajuu nèti sorga do, hud'i laa Lamatua hia ne mamadhe-mamopo!<bt>Be careful! Cuz (elaboration), later God2 will punish that person/s who comes teaching Good News which is not the same as that which we-exc previously taught (doublet). Even if that person is from us-exc or, God2's underling from heaven (*angel) or [whoever], may God2 give him/her an accursed fate/death!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="soo-subha = (UNS says kutuk) implies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">soo-subha = (UNS says kutuk) implies langgar sumpah ; UNS dhoo = sumpah ; dhoo-saseo = curse ; saseo = kutuk (manusia; but clashes with God as agent)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tatu nèngu lèke soo-subha!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">tatu nèngu lèke soo-subha!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anathema: accursed, cursed, damned, condemned to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">anathema: accursed, cursed, damned, condemned to Hell, set apart for destruction LITERALLY: But even if we or an angel from Heaven preach another "good news" to you, different from what we preached, let him be cursed.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ji'i dhu peka le karèi nèti uru ka. Te ngaa limuri ne, ja'a neo hari pasanèd'e sèmi ne'e: ladhe abhu dhèu dhu aj'a leo nèti Lii Lolo Be'a dhu miu abhu le uru èèna, hud'i laa Lamatua hia ne mamadhe-mamopo.<bt>We-exc have really already told these things from before. But now I want to remind [you] again, like this: if there is a person who comes teaching different from that Good News which previously you accepted/obtained/possessed/got, may God2 give him/her an accursed fate/death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As we have said before,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As we have said before, so I say again, if anyone preaches another "good news'" to you, different from what you received, let him be cursed.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ja'a bani peka sèmi èèna, lula ja'a neo pakarej'e d'ara Ama Lamatua, neo boe pakarej'e dhèu rai-haha ne. Miu ngee, na, ja'a tenge kolongara nèti dhèu rai-haha, do? Aad'o! Te ladhe ja'a tao sèmi èèna, ja'a pantas boe j'aj'i ana pua-paleha nèti Kristus.<bt>I dare to speak like that, because I want to make God2's insides happy, not want to please human's insides. Do you think I want to seek name/reputation (=please) among humans, [tag question]? No! Cuz (elaboration) if I did like that, well, I would not be appropriate/worthy to be Kristus' slave/servant (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="neo laa = sangka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">neo laa = sangka</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Am I now looking for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Am I now looking for people's approval or God's? Or do I try to please people? If people's approval, then I would no longer be a servant [slave] of Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus lole hari tasamia ka na j'aj'i dhèu pajuu-paleha Lamatua Yesus<bt>Paulus retells how he came to be the Lord Yesus' envoy (*apostle)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Ja'a peka paled'a dènge miu, na, Lii Lolo Be'a dhu ja'a aj'a-nori miu, nèti boe tatao dhèu rai-haha.<bt>Siblings! I want to tell [you] very explicitly/clearly that, that Good News which I taught (doublet) you, it's not humans who created it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I want you to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I want you to know, brothers, the Good News which I preached is not according to people;</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Ja'a abhu boe nèti dhèu rai-haha, aa abhu boe ca dhèu sa dhu aj'a-nori ja'a. Te Yesus Kristus mesa Na ka dhu bhoke sasoa na mi ja'a.<bt>I did not receive/get [it] from humans, and it's not humans who taught it to me. Cuz (elaboration) it's Yesus Kristus himself who opened/revealed it's meaning to me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Neither did I receive it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Neither did I receive it from people, nor was I taught it, but by revelation of Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Tatu miu tadèngi le lii lolo nèti j'ara mamuri ja'a, lod'o ja'a madhutu agama Yahudi era, si? Lod'o èèna, ja'a paj'èra titu kèna dhèu-dhèu unu Lamatua, aa neo pa'ele iie aa'i si.<bt>Surely you have heard the story about my life, when I still followed/obeyed the Yahudi religion, right? At that time, I mistreated/cause to suffer very badly God2's people wanting to completely destroy them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kèd'u"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">kèd'u</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="porthew: destroy, annihilate, make havoc of,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">porthew: destroy, annihilate, make havoc of, ravage, waste LITERALLY: For you heard of my past way of life in the Jewish religion, that I persecuted the church of God excessively, and destroyed it.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 8:3, 22:4-5, 26:9-11</note><v n="14" />Aa lod'o èèna kahèi, d'ara ja'a neo titu kèna aj'a j'ara-j'ara agama Yahudi, risi nèti dhèu Yahudi dhu leo dhu ca dadena dènge ja'a. Aa ja'a ne maj'èni risi pakako ad'a bèi-baki èdhi dènge atora agama aa'i-aa'i.<bt>And at that time also, my insides yearned to learn/teach/study the Yahudi religion, more than other Yahudi people who were the same age-grade as me. And I here was more/most diligent in carrying out all our-ex ancestors' traditions and religious regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ca dadena = age mates, sebaya,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">ca dadena = age mates, sebaya, sebatang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prokoptw: go forward, go ahead, advance,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">prokoptw: go forward, go ahead, advance, excel sunelikiwtes: contemporary, same age group<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>zelotes: enthusiast, burn out for something, zealot, to do and defend something paradosis: tradition, custom<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: and I went ahead in the Jewish religion beyond many Jews my age, being more zealous in the traditions of my ancestors.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 22:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15-16" />Masi ka sèmi èèna, Ama Lamatua dhu pama'ète nare le ho patadhe Ana Na mi ja'a. Ina ku dhae nara iisi mèka ja'a, te Nèngu dhu hag'e mema le ja'a, lula Na neo pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na mi ja'a. Nèngu kahèi pua ja'a ho laku peka-padhai dènge dhèu Yahudi boe sèra. Lod'o Na pua ja'a èèna, laku boe manèngi a'abhu nèti dhèu leo.<bt>Even though it was like that, nevertheless God decided to introduce His Child to me. My mother had not yet given birth to me (=before she...), [contrary to expectation] He had already chose me ahead.of.time, because He want to show his goodness/kindness/ grace/mercy to me. He also sent/commissioned me, to go speak/bring message to the non Yahudi people. When He commissioned me like that, I did not go request other people/person's advice/opinions.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But when the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But when the one who set me apart from birth, and called me by his grace, was pleased LITERALLY: to reveal his Son in me so that I might preach him among the non-Jews, immediately I did not consult any person,<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:15-16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 9:3-6, 22:6-10, 26:13-18</note><v n="17" />Aa laku boe paraga dènge dhèu heka-dhèu heka Kristen dhu j'aj'i mema le dhèu pajuu-paleha Yesus ètu kota Yerusalem. Te ngaa laku dènge ka asa rai Arab. Èle ka, ja'a lèpa hari asa kota Damsik.<bt>And I also did not go meet the Kristen elders who were already Yesus' apostles beforehand in the city of Yerusalem. But I went straight.away to Arab land/country. After that, I came back again to Damsik city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: nor did I go up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: nor did I go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before me, but I went into Arabia, and returned again to Damascus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Hèia lalu eele tèlu tèu ku, heka laku paraga dènge Petrus<bt>After three years, then I went to meet Petrus</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lalu eele = setelah, lewat (time)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">lalu eele = setelah, lewat (time)</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:18" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Lii Yunani dhu suri ètu ayat ne'e pake ngara <span class="Italic">Kefas</span>. Èèna ngara leo nèti Petrus madhutu lii Aram. Petrus ne, ngara madhutu lii Yunani. Te ngaa dua ngara se, sasoa na èci èèna ka, nuka &lt;&lt;hadhu&gt;&gt;.<bt>The Greek writing in this verse uses the name, <span class="Italic">Kefas.</span> That was Petrus' other name according to the Aram language. That Petrus, [is] his name according to the Greek language. But the meaning of those two names, [are] the same, that is ‘rock’.</bt></note>ètu Yerusalem, ho pakarèi j'ara-j'ara nèti nèngu. Ka ja'a manubha taha canguru lèmi lod'o ètu nèi.<bt>[CHECK younger generation for pakanucu] in Yerusalem to find/get information from him. And I stayed temporarily there for fifteen days. [EXEG: Gk /istorew/ “to visit, with the purpose of obtaining information” LN; “inquire, get information from” BADG. Note some commentators (e.g. Habermas) feel this Gk lexical choice is highly significant for a variety of reasons, so it's worth saying more than just ‘visit’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakanucu = [Lena not know; UNSs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">pakanucu = [Lena not know; UNSs not know both] berunding (mencari tahu hal-hal yang belum diketahui, sampai halus), pertimbangkan sesuatu sampai halus-halus</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then after three years I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then after three years I went to Jerusalem to visit [and get information from] Cephas [Peter], and stayed with him fifteen days;</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 9:26-30</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Lod'o èèna, ja'a paraga kahèi dènge Yakobis, ari d'èlu Lamatua Yesus. Te ngaa ja'a paraga boe dènge dhèu pajuu-paleha Lamatua dhu leo sèra. Dhoka dua ra di.<bt>At that time, I also met with the Lord Yesus' birth younger.sibling (=not a cousin, but from same parent/s), named Yakobis. But I did not meet with God2's other apostles. Only just those two. [EXEG: LN notes that /adelphos/ with a meaning of ‘cousin’ is not attested, in spite of church tradition. NOTE to daughter translations: /adi/ is probably sufficient here, and would avoid unnecessary disputes with RC that might result in hesitance to use or promote the scriptures.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I didn't see other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I didn't see other apostles, only James, the brother of the Lord.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ngaa dhu ja'a suri ne, mema tare'a sèmi èèna! Ja'a kapod'e boe! Lamatua ne'a aa'i!<bt>What I'm writing here, [it's] really true like that! I'm not twisting/decieving! God2 knows it all! [=adds emphasis/authority/legitimacy]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Look, the things I write"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Look, the things I write to you, before God I am not lying.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Èle èèna, hèia ja'a laku asa propensi Siria dènge propensi Kilikia.<bt>After that, then I went to Siria province and Kilikia province.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then I came into the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then I came into the region of Syria and Cilicia.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Lod'o èèna, dhèu-dhèu unu Kristus ètu propensi Yudea, dhae tadhe mèka ja'a.<bt>At that time, Kristus' people in Yudea province had not yet met me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I was unknown personally to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I was unknown personally to the churches of Judea which are in Christ,</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Dhèu se'e dhoka tadèngi lii palolo, dhu peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu uru èèna paj'èra èdhi, limuri ne nuka aj'a Lii Lolo Be'a Kristus. Nèngu ka dhu uru èèna, neo pa'ele iie aa'i èdhi.&gt;&gt;<bt>They had only heard news/stories saying, &lt;&lt;That person who previously tormented us, now he is teaching Kristus' Good News. He is the one who previously wanted to completely destroy us.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They had only heard that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They had only heard that "The one who persecuted us before now preaches the Good News by faith which he once destroyed,"</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ropa ra tadèngi sèmi èèna, aa'i-aa'i ra koa-kio Ama Lamatua, lula ja'a parcaya le Yesus Kristus.<bt>Hearing like.that, then they all praised (doublet) God, because I had believed in Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and they glorified God because"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and they glorified God because of me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu pajuu-paleha dhu leo sèra, sèmi rare a'aj'a Paulus dènge be'a<bt>The Lord Yesus' other apostles accept Paulus' teaching well</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />D'ai èle canguru èpa tèu, hèia ja'a lèpa asa kota Yerusalem sama-sama dènge Barnabas. Aa ji'i ngèti dènge Titus, ca dhèu parcaya dhu Yahudi boe.<bt>After fourteen years, then I went back again to the city of Yerusalem together with Barnabas. And we-ex also brought Titus, a non Yahudi believer.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anabainw: go up sumparalambanw: take along|i(1)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">anabainw: go up sumparalambanw: take along<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: After fourteen years I went up to Jerusalem again with Barnabas, taking Titus too;</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo nèti Dhèu Pajuu-paleha 11:30, 15:2</note><v n="2" />Ja'a laku asa nèi, lula lii paredha Ama Lamatua. D'ai nèi, ka ja'a lole mi dhèu heka-dhèu heka Kristen, Lii Lolo Be'a dhu ja'a aj'a-nori le mi dhèu Yahudi boe sèra. Lod'o èèna, ja'a peka unu ku mi rèngu se, ho ra parisa pabe'a-be'a ngaa dhu ja'a aj'a le sèra, lèke do aad'o. Te ladhe ra pama'ète, peka na, a'aj'a ja'a èèna sala, na, dhèu bisa ngee, na, ja'a sab'a iia d'ara di!<bt>I went there because God [is] who ordered. Arriving there (remote), then I storied/reported to the Kristen elders, that Good News which I had taught (doublet) to the non Yahudi people. At that time, I spoke by myself with them, so that they could examine carefully that which I taught, [whether it was] true or not. Cuz (elaboration) if they decided that my teaching was wrong, well, people could think that my work [is] just ineffectual/in.vain/ pointless!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apokalupsis: revelation anatithemi: to declare, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">apokalupsis: revelation anatithemi: to declare, to explain, to set before someone, to communicate something<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>kerussw: to announce, to preach dokew: to seem, to be influential, to be recognized as being something, to have a reputation<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>me pws: lest somehow kenos: empty, useless, in vain, for nothing<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>trexw: run LITERALLY: but I went up by revelation, and explained to them the gospel which I preach among the nations, but privately to those who were of repute, lest somehow I was running or had run in vain.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ropa dhèu se'e tadèngi rare lii ja'a sèmi èèna, hèia ra sèmi rare dènge be'a. Aa ra d'èi sèmi rare Titus dènge be'a kahèi. Masi ka Titus dhèu Yahudi boe, te ngaa ra laka-seti boe sèna ka na suna.<bt>Hearing my speaking like that, then they accepted [it] well. They also accepted Titus well. Even though he was a non Yahudi person, nevertheless they did not force him to get circumcised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ change all occurrences of laka-seti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">@@ change all occurrences of laka-seti</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anagkazw: to force, to compel, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">anagkazw: to force, to compel, to make someone do something peritemnw: to be circumcised<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: But even Titus, who was with me, being a Greek, was not forced to be circumcised.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te ngaa lod'o èèna, abhu a'ari dhèu pèri dhu d'èi boe a'aj'a ja'a, lula rèngu se aj'a dhu leo. Rèngu se, dhèu Kristen kapod'e-kabèli. Ka rèngu mau-mau mai laka-seti dhèu unu Kristus sèra dhu dhèu Yahudi boe, ho madhutu aa'i atora agama Yahudi. Te ngaa, lula Yesus Kristus patalale eele le èdhi, nèti èèna ka atora sèra èki heka èdhi, sèmi ènu sa.<bt>But at that time, there were several siblings who did not agree with my teaching, because they taught differently. These people are false/deceptive Kristen. So they came quietly/secretly to force Kristus' people who are not Yahudi, to follow all the Yahudi people's religious regulations. But because Yesus Kristus has already freed us-inc, that.is.why we-inc are no longer tied/bound by those regulations, like a slave.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pareisaktos: sneak in pseudadelphos: false brother|i(4)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">pareisaktos: sneak in pseudadelphos: false brother<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>pareisepxomai: slip in kataskopew: spy out<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>eleutheria: freedom, liberty [from slavery to the law] katadoulow: to make slaves, to enslave, to bring into bondage<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: But because of false brothers who sneaked in secretly, slipping in to spy out our freedom which we have in Christ Jesus, in order to make us slaves;</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Masi ka ra laka-seti sèmi èèna, te ngaa ciki sa ji'i ngo'o boe sèmi ngare. Dènge j'ara ne'e, miu bisa parcaya taruu Lii Lolo Be'a dhu ja'a nori le. Te dhu mola-mola na kèna!<bt>Even though they forced like.that, nevertheless we-in did not accept even a little. In that way, you-pl can continue to believe the Good News which I have taught. Cuz (elaboration) it is absolutely true!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pij'i = pungut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">pij'i = pungut</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eixw: yield, give in, submit hupotage:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">eixw: yield, give in, submit hupotage: subjection, submission<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>diamenw: remain, stay, continue LITERALLY: We did not give in to them for a moment, so that the truth of the gospel might remain for you.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dhèu heka-dhèu heka se sèmi rare lii a'aj'a ja'a ne, aa ra patabha heka ngaa-ngaa. Te ngaa Ama Lamatua hag'e boe dhèu. De masi ka rèngu dhèu kapai do ana iiki, ngaa-ngaa tao boe.<bt>Those elders accepted my teaching [wholeheartedly], and they did not add anything else. But God does not discriminate/differentiate. So (consequently), whether they or big/important people or small, that's not what is important.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ngaa-ngaa tao boe = it makes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">ngaa-ngaa tao boe = it makes no difference</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hopoios: what kind, what sort diapherw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">hopoios: what kind, what sort diapherw: to make a difference, to matter<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>lambanw: receive prosanatithemi: to add<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: and from those who seemed to be [important / leaders]--what kind they were makes no difference to me--God does not receive a man by appearances--they added nothing to me,</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 10:17</note><v n="7" />Te dhu lèke, nuka: rèngu re'a, na, Ama Lamatua pili nare le ja'a, ho kèti Lii Lolo Be'a mi dhèu-dhèu Yahudi boe. Nuka sèmi dhu Na paredha mi Petrus kahèi, sèna ka nèti Lii Lolo Be'a asa dhèu Yahudi.<bt>What is true/significant, is: they know that God has already chosen me to go take the Good News to non Yahudi people. The same as He also commisioned Petrus to take the Good News to Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="enantion: before akrobustia: heathenism, paganism, Gentiles|i(7)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">enantion: before akrobustia: heathenism, paganism, Gentiles<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: but on the contrary, they saw that I was entrusted to the heathen, just as Peter to the circumcised,</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te Ama Lamatua pangèd'u koasa mi Petrus ho j'aj'i dhèu pajuu-paleha mi dhèu Yahudi. Sèmi èèna kahèi, Na hia ja'a koasa sèna ka j'aj'i dhèu pajuu-paleha mi dhèu-dhèu dhu Yahudi boe.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God has given power/authority to Petrus to become an apostle for the Yahudi people. Like that also He gave power/authority to me to become an apostle for the non Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="energew: to work, to be at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">energew: to work, to be at work, to operate, to be effective LITERALLY: for the one who worked in Peter for an apostleship to the circumcised, worked in me to the Gentiles.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Lod'o èèna, madhutu ngangee dhèu sèra, Yakobis, Petrus,<bt>At that time, people already considered Yakobis, Petrus</bt><note reference="2:9" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri madhutu lii Yunani ètu ayat ne'e pake ngara <span class="Italic">Kefas</span>. Ngara leo nèti Petrus.<bt>The Greek language writing in this verse uses the name, <span class="Italic">Kefas.</span> That [is] Petrus' other name.</bt></note>dènge Yohanis, dhu j'aj'i le ama-ama gareja. Ropa rèngu tèlu ra re'a, na, Ama Lamatua pad'elo le d'ara hua iia Na mi ja'a, hèia ra kèd'i paj'ola ai dènge ja'a, aa dènge Barnabas, sèna ka j'aj'i mi tadha, peka na, ji'i aa'i-aa'i mi d'ara èci le. Rèngu ro'o kahèi, ji'i ngèti Lii Lolo Be'a asa dhèu Yahudi boe, aa rèngu rèti asa dhèu Yahudi.<bt>and Yohanis, to be church leaders. When the three of them found out that God has shown His goodness/kindness/grace/ generosity/mercy to me, then they stood and shook hands with me and Barnabas, as a sign/signal that we-ex all were of one insides (=in agreement). They wanted for us to take the Good News to the non Yahudi people, and they take it to the Yahudi people. [NOTE to daughter translations: “they stood up to come shake hands with me” is to emphasize the honour of extending the “right hand of fellowship”; initiated by the important people]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paj'ola ai = berjabat tangan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">paj'ola ai = berjabat tangan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and when they knew [of]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and when they knew [of] the grace that was given to me, James and Cephas and John, who seemed to be pillars, gave me and Barnabas the right hand of fellowship, that we should go to the Gentiles, and they to the circumcision;</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Dhoka ca j'ara di, dhu ra pasanèd'e ji'i, nuka ji'i baku bhèlu soru-bara dhèu dhu unu aad'o sèra. Mema j'ara ne'e ka dhu ja'a neo tao.<bt>There was just one matter which they reminded me of, that is that we-exc don't forget to help (doublet) the poor people. That is truly what I already want to do.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: only they would have us"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: only they would have us remember the poor, which very thing I was eager to do.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus kai Petrus ètu Antiokia, lula na pakaj'èu nèti dhèu Yahudi boe<bt>Paulus rebukes Petrus in Antiokia, because he distanced himself from non Yahudi people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ka ca tèka, Petrus mai asa kota Antiokia. Hèia ja'a kai ne patoo madha dènge madha, lula nèngu tao sala.<bt>Then one time Petrus come to Antiokia city. Then2 I rebuked him face to face, because he was doing wrong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="antistemi: to be set against, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">antistemi: to be set against, to oppose kataginwskw: to condemn, to accuse, to pronounce guilty<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: But when Cephas came to Antioch, I opposed him to his face, because he stood condemned.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Lod'o na heka mai, nèngu karèj'e madhèdi na'a dènge dhèu-dhèu unu Kristus dhu dhèu Yahudi boe. Te ngaa ropa angalai Yakobis dhèu Yahudi sèra mai, hèia Petrus mulai pakaj'èu nèti a'ari dhèu Yahudi boe, ka na na'a pa'èci heka dènge rèngu. Te lula na madha'u dènge a'aj'a nèti dhèu Yahudi dhu peka na, dhèu unu Kristus hud'i kèpe pa'èra-èra atora agama Yahudi aa'i-aa'i, aa hud'i pakaj'èu ku dènge dhèu-dhèu dhu Yahudi boe.<bt>When he had just come, he was happy to sit eating together with Kristus' non Yahudi people. But then Yakobis' Yahudi friends came, then/so Petrus began to distance/separate himself from the non Yahudi siblings, and did not eat anymore with them. Because he was afraid of those Yahudi people who teach saying, Kristus' people must tightly hold (=follow) tightly all the Yahudi people's religious regulations, and [they] must live separated from non Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunesthiw: to eat with hupostellw: to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">sunesthiw: to eat with hupostellw: to withdraw, to go back from<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>aphorizw: to separate phobew: to fear, to be afraid<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: For before certain ones came from James, he ate with the Gentiles; but when they came, he withdrew and separated himself, fearing the circumcision party</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ropa rèdhi tatao Petrus ne, ka dhèu Yahudi dhu leo sèra tao madhutu kahèi. Toke Barnabas kahèi madhutu tatao ra dhu peka leo, tao leo.<bt>Seeing Petrus' aforementioned behaviour, other Yahudi people also followed along. To.the.point.that Barnabas also followed their behaviour which spoke different did different (=hypocrisy).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunupokrinomai: to join in pretending, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">sunupokrinomai: to join in pretending, to join in hypocrisy sunapagw: to carry away, to yield, to lead away, to lead astray<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>hupokrisis: hypocrisy LITERALLY: The rest of the Jews joined him in hypocrisy, so that even Barnabas was led astray by their hypocrisy.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Te ngaa ropa ja'a patigi kèdhi, rèngu madhutu be'a heka dad'èi Lii Lolo Be'a, hèia ja'a kai dènge ka Petrus ètu katanga madha rèngu aa'i-aa'i ra, peka na, &lt;&lt;Eee, Petrus! Èu ne, mema dhèu Yahudi. Te ngaa Ama Lamatua bhoke le j'ara, ho dhèu dhu parcaya Yesus Kristus pa'èki heka madhutu atora agama Yahudi sèra. Aa èu dhu sèmi more le j'ara ne'e, nga tasamia ka, èu laka-seti dhèu Yahudi boe, sèna ka tao iisi ra sama sèmi dhèu Yahudi?&gt;&gt;<bt>But when I saw that they did not correctly follow the Good New's intent, then I right.away scolded Petrus in front of all of them, saying, &lt;&lt;Eee, Petrus! You are truly/certainly a Yahudi person. But God is the one who has opened the way so that people who believe in Yesus Kristus are no longer tied with/bound to the Yahudi people's religious regulations. And you have accepted that matter, so how is it that now you still want to force non Yahudi people so that they make themselves like Yahudi people?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orthopodeoo: be straightforward, be unwavering, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">orthopodeoo: be straightforward, be unwavering, be sincere in conduct LITERALLY: But when I saw that they were not straightforward about the truth of the gospel, I said to Peter in front of them all, "If you, being a Jew, live like a Gentile and not like a Jew, how come you force the Gentiles to live like Jews?"<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ja'a kai Petrus sèmi èèna, lula ji'i dua mi dhèu Yahudi. Suku ji'i dua mi se dhèu Yahudi, sama boe dènge suku leo sèra, lula suku ji'i dhu nèbhu le tadhe Ama Lamatua.<bt>I scolded/rebuked Petrus like that, because the two of us were both Yahudi people. Our Yahudi nation/tribe/race is not the same as other nations, because our nation has already known God for a long time.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="udhu-rasa = 4 UNS not know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">udhu-rasa = 4 UNS not know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We who are Jews by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We who are Jews by birth, and not Gentile sinners,</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Te ngaa limuri ne, ji'i nge'a kahèi, na, Lamatua sèmi nare boe ca dhèu sa j'aj'i mi dhèu mola, lula nèngu tao madhutu atora agama dènge be'a. Te ngaa Lamatua sèmi nare dhèu, ladhe nèngu parcaya Yesus Kristus, lula boe nèti nèngu madhutu atora agama. Sèmi èèna ku, heka Lamatua peka na, dhèu ne dènge heka sasala-sasigo.<bt>But now we-inc also know that, God2 does not accept even one person as straight/just/righteous, because s/he acts well according to religious regulations. But God2 accepts a person, if s/he believes Yesus Kristus, not because s/he acts according to religious regulations. Like that, only then does God2 say a person as innocent (=no longer having wrong/sin).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: knowing that a person is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: knowing that a person is not justified by the works of the law, but by faith in Jesus Christ, and we trust in Christ Jesus, so that we are justified by faith in Christ, and not be the works of the law, because by the works of the law no human being is justified.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Sod'a Koa-Kio 143:2, Roma 3:20, 22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Nèti èèna ka, ji'i aj'a, na, Lamatua sèmi nare dhèu j'aj'i mi dhèu mola, lula na parcaya Yesus Kristus. Te ngaa abhu dhèu Yahudi dhu pasala ji'i. Ra peka na, ji'i parcaya Yesus Kristus, te ngaa kèpe heka atora agama Yahudi. Miu neo pèci sasala sèmi èèna mi ji'i kahèi, do?<bt>That's why we-exc teach that God accepts a person as straight/right because s/he believes in Yesus Kristus. But there are Yahudi people who accuse us-ex. They say we believe in Kristus, but no longer hold the Yahudi religious regulations. Do you also want to throw an accusation like that, [tag question]?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te ngaa abhu dhèu Yahudi dhu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">Te ngaa abhu dhèu Yahudi dhu galaa ji'i peka na, ji'i sala, lula ji'i parcaya Yesus Kristus, te ngaa madhutu heka atora agama Yahudi.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if in our attempt"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if in our attempt to be justified in Christ, we ourselves are found to be sinners, then is Christ a servant of sin? Certainly not!</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te ladhe ja'a kèpe kore hari atora agama dhu ja'a patabuli eele le, èèna heka peka na ja'a sala kèna!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if I hold again those aforementioned religious regulations which I have already gotten free of, well then I'd be wrong!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kataluw: destroy oikodomew: build up|i(18) (18)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">kataluw: destroy oikodomew: build up<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>parabates: transgression, break the law sunistemi: demonstrate, prove<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: For if I rebuild the things which I destroyed, I prove that I am a lawbreaker.</Message></Annotation><v n="19-20" />Mema uru èèna, ja'a tenge j'ara ho madhutu dènge be'a atora agama Yahudi, sèna ka ja'a pabe'a dènge Lamatua. Te ngaa bisa boe kahèi. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a tèke eele le atora agama sèra, ho mamuri pa'èki dènge Kristus. Dènge j'ara sèmi ne'e, heka Ama Lamatua sèmi nare ja'a j'aj'i mi dhèu mola. Peka sèmi ne'e ka: ja'a madhe lèke paku ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha sama-sama dènge Kristus. De limuri ne, ja'a boe ka dhu mamuri, te ngaa Kristus ka dhu mamuri ètu d'ara ngi'u ja'a. Ja'a abhu mamuri dhu hiu ne, lula parcaya Ana nèti Lamatua. Te Nèngu sue ja'a titu kèna, toke Na madhe gati ja'a.<bt>It's true that previously I tried to carefully follow/obey the Yahudi religious regulations, so that I could be in a reciprocally.good.relationship with God2. But it wasn't possible. That's why now I have left behind/ abandoned those regulations to live tied/bound to Kristus. In doing like that, only then does God accept me as a straight/just person. Just regard it as if, I have died nailed to the cross together with Kristus. So (consequently) now it's not me who lives, but Kristus who lives in my self/being. I got this life which is new, because I believe in God2's Child. Cuz (elaboration) he greatly loves me, to.the.point that He died replacing me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For through the law, I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For through the law, I died to the law, that I might live to God. LITERALLY: I have been crucified with Christ. It is no longer I who live, but Christ lives in me. And the life that I now live in the flesh, I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me, and gave himself for me.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Hèia Ama Lamatua sèmi nare ja'a, lula d'ara hua iia Na, lula boe nèti ja'a madhutu atora agama sèra. Te ladhe dhèu bisa pabe'a dènge Lamatua lula madhutu atora agama, èèna sasoa na, mamadhe Kristus iia-iia d'ara di.<bt>Thus, God recieves me because of His goodness/kindness/grace/mercy, not because I follow religious regulations. Cuz (elaboration) if people could be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2 because of following religious regulations, that would mean that, the death of Kristus' was just pointless/in.vain.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I do not nullify the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I do not nullify the grace of God. For if righteousness could be gained through the law, Christ died for nothing.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Sèra sa ka dhu ja'a peka dènge Petrus si ètu Antiokia.<bt>That there, [is] what I told to Petrus mob in Antiokia.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ama Lamatua sèmi nare èdhi j'aj'i mi dhèu mola, lula èdhi parcaya Yesus Kristus<bt>God accepts us-inc as straight/just people, because we believe in Yesus Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Heh! Dhèu Galati sèra! Uru èèna, ja'a unu ku lole dènge miu patoo madha dènge madha, lula-nèti mamadhe Yesus Kristus ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha. Te ngaa limuri ne dhèu monya miu mamadha iia-iia! Miu se, goa titu kèna!<bt>Heh! Galatia people! Previously I myself have explained to you face to face, about Yesus Kristus' death on the cross. But now people have easily decieved you! Your stupidity is too much!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="unu = myself (emphasizing authority here)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">unu = myself (emphasizing authority here) ; mesa = myself (without anyone else) ; mamadha mea-mea (UNS not like) = sonde rasa = KM tipu manta-manta = talalu gampang kana tipu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anoetos: unintelligent, foolish baskainw: to bewitch,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">anoetos: unintelligent, foolish baskainw: to bewitch, hex, cast a spell on<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>peithw: to obey prographw: to present clearly to, to portray to, to describe plainly, to openly display<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>staurow: to crucify LITERALLY: O foolish Galatians! Who has bewitched you that you do not obey the truth? Jesus Christ was clearly presented as crucified before your eyes.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ja'a neo dhoka karèi ca j'ara di. Miu sèmi mere le Roh Lamatua èèna, lula miu madhutu atora agama, do? Aad'o, si! Roh Na mai asa miu, lula miu lèka Lii Lolo Be'a dhu miu nanene èèna.<bt>I only want to ask one thing. Did you recieve that Spirit of God2's, because you followed religious regulations, [tag question]? Of course not, right! His Spirit came to you, because you believed that Good News which you had heard.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akoe: report manthanw: find out, learn|i(2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">akoe: report manthanw: find out, learn<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: This only I would like to find out from you: Did you receive the Spirit by doing the Law, or by hearing with faith?</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />De, nga tao ka miu goa sèmi èèna, ee? Uru èèna, miu mamuri le madhutu dad'èi Roh Mola-Mèci. Te ngaa limuri ne, miu kabèli hari, mamuri madhutu dad'èi dhèu rai-haha.<bt>So (consequently), why are you-pl so stupid like that, ee? Previously you lived according to the Holy Spirit's will. But now you have turned again to live according to human's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epitelew: to finish, to end, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">epitelew: to finish, to end, to complete something, to perfect LITERALLY: Are you so foolish? After starting with the Spirit, are you finishing by the flesh?<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Lod'o hiu-hiu dhu miu parcaya Kristus èèna, miu abhu j'aj'èra ae titu kèna. Mage dhoka j'ara sèra ele iia d'ara di! (Te ngaa madhutu mola-mola na, parcaya mi Kristus ele boe iia d'ara.)<bt>When you just began to believe in Kristus, you got/experienced much suffering. Don't let it be that all of that become pointless! (But in fact, believing in Kristus cannot be pointless.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasxw: to experience, to undergo, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">pasxw: to experience, to undergo, to suffer eike: in vain, for nothing<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: Have you experienced so many things in vain? If it is in vain.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Lod'o Ama Lamatua hia Roh Na, aa pad'elo rupa-rupa tadha malaa ètu madha miu, miu ngee, na, Lamatua tao sèmi èèna, lula miu madhutu atora agama, do? Aad'o, si! Na tao sèmi èèna, lula miu lèka Lii Lolo Be'a dhu miu nanene èèna.<bt>When God gave His Spirit, and showed those various kinds of miracles in front of you, did you think He did like that because you follow religious regulations, [tag question]? Of course not, right! He did like that, because you believed that Good News which you had heard.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epixoregew: give plenty, supply abundantly LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">epixoregew: give plenty, supply abundantly LITERALLY: Therefore, he who gives the Spirit to you, and does miracles among you, does he do it by the deeds of the Law, or by hearing with faith?<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Sanèd'e mèdhi era sina ma, bèi-baki dhèu Yahudi, nuka Abraham. Te Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua suri, peka na, &lt;&lt;Lula na parcaya Ama Lamatua, ka Lamatua sèmi nare ne j'aj'i mi dhèu mola.&gt;&gt;<bt>Don't you still remember the Yahudi people's ancestor, that is grandfather/forefather Abraham. Cuz (elaboration) the Scriptures write, saying, “Because he believed God, that's why God2 accepted him as a straight/just person.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="logizomai: to count, to reckon LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">logizomai: to count, to reckon LITERALLY: Just as Abraham trusted God, and it was counted to him as righteousness.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 15:6, Roma 4:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />De miu hud'i me'a pabe'a-be'a ku j'ara ne'e! Dhèu dhu parcaya sama sèmi Abraham, rèngu j'aj'i mi dhèu unu Ama Lamatua dhu tare'a-re'a.<bt>So (consequently) you must understand this matter well! People who believe like Abraham, they become God's true people. [Translator's Notes]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then know this, that those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then know this, that those who believe, they are children of Abraham.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani uru sèra, peka na, &lt;&lt;rèngu j'aj'i ana-ana Abraham&gt;&gt;. Dhèu Yahudi biasa pake lii pakasame &lt;ana-ana Abraham&gt; dènge sasoa na, &lt;dhèu unu Ama Lamatua&gt;. Baca kahèi ètu <span class="Italic">Roma</span> 4:16.<bt>The original Greek language Bible writes, saying, “they became Abraham's children”. The Yahudi people often use the term ‘Abraham's children’ with the meaning of ‘God's children’. See also <span class="Italic">Roma </span>4:16.</bt></note><v n="8" />Lamatua dhu peka tèke le ètu d'ara Sasuri Mola-Mèci Na, peka na, Nèngu sèmi nare kahèi dhèu nèti suku leo j'aj'i mi dhèu mola, ladhe ra parcaya Ne. Te uru èèna, Na peka mema le mi Abraham Lii Lolo Be'a, na, &lt;&lt;Bèli-camèd'a suku aa'i-aa'i ètu rai-haha ne, abhu mèngi-nale lula èu ne.&gt;&gt;<bt>God2 told ahead.of.time in His Holy Writing that, He would also recieve people from other nations/tribes as straight/just people, if they believed in Him. Cuz (elaboration) long ago He already foretold the Good News to Abraham saying, “Later all people/nations on earth will get/receive blessing because of you.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dikaiow: to justify, to make right,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">dikaiow: to justify, to make right, to make right with God eneulogew: to bless<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>proeuaggelizomai: proclaim in advance, preach ahead of time prooraw: see previously, see in advance, see ahead of time<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: And the Scripture, forseeing that God would justify the nations by faith, preached before the Good News to Abraham, saying, "In you shall all the nations be blessed".</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 12:3</note><v n="9" />Lula lii moa Ama Lamatua èèna, ka Na papuru kahèi berkat mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu parcaya Ne, nuka sèmi dhu Na hia mi Abraham.<bt>Because of that promise of God's, He also handed down blessing2 to all people who believe in Him, just like He already gave2 to Abraham.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eulogew: to bless LITERALLY: So those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">eulogew: to bless LITERALLY: So those who believe are blessed with Abraham, who believed.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dhèu dhu madhutu atora agama, sèna ka Lamatua sèmi nare ne j'aj'i mi dhèu mola, nèngu hud'i pasae nare ku babia nèti atora sèra aa'i-aa'i, nuka sèmi nèngu lèke le dhoo. Te dhu suri ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu madhutu boe taruu atora agama d'ai lutu, nèngu lèke le dhoo èèna!&gt;&gt;<bt>A person who follows religious regulations so that God2 will accept him/her as a straight/just person, na, s/he must shoulder.carry the burden/weight of all those regulations, just like s/he has been affected by a curse. Cuz (elaboration) it is written in the Holy Writings, saying, “The person who does not continually follow religious regulations down to the fine detail, s/he is cursed!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katara: curse epikataratos: cursed, be under"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">katara: curse epikataratos: cursed, be under divine wrath, awaiting the final destruction<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>emmenw: persevere in, stand by, be careful to obey LITERALLY: For as many as are of the works of the law are under a curse. For it has been written, &lt;&lt;Cursed is everyone who does not continue to do all things which have been written in the book of the Law.&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 27:26</note><v n="11" />Te ngaa te'a, na, Ama Lamatua sèmi nare boe ca dhèu sa, lula na madhutu atora agama. Te dhu suri tèke, peka na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu hud'i parcaya ku Ja'a, heka sèmi kore ne j'aj'i mi dhèu mola, ho na abhu mamuri dhu lèke.&gt;&gt;<bt>But it is already clear/we already know, God does not accept a person, because s/he follows religious regulations. Cuz (elaboration) it is written, saying, “A person must believe in Me, before I will accept him/her as a straight/righteous person, so.that s/he can get/have true life.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="delos: be clear LITERALLY: It is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">delos: be clear LITERALLY: It is clear that no person is justified by the Law in God's sight, for, "The one who is justified by faith will live."<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Habakuk 2:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />De ladhe dhèu neo mamuri madhutu dad'èi atora agama, nèngu hud'i tao madhutu ku aa'i-aa'i toke lutu! Te Lamatua dhu peka mema le ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci, na, &lt;&lt;Dhèu dhu neo mamuri madhutu atora, èèna na nèngu bhute dhoka dènge atora sèra di.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), if a person wants to live according to the way of religious regulations, s/he must do according to them all down to the fine detail! Cuz (elaboration) God2 has foretold in His Holy Writing saying, “The person who lives following regulations, later s/he will be totally preoccupied/busy with those regulations.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Law is not based"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Law is not based on believing; but, "The person who does these things will live by them."</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Atora nèti Ama-ama Agama 18:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Te ngaa Kristus b'ae pama'ète le, ho patabuli èdhi nèti atora agama dhu èki èdhi. Uru èèna, èdhi mamuri oe madhe, dènge pasae babia atora agama, nuka sèmi dhèu dhu lèke dhoo. Te ngaa limuri ne Lamatua Yesus ded'e eele le babia èèna nèti èdhi. Te dhu suri tèke ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci, na, &lt;&lt;Ladhe dhèu madhe lèke kadhoe ètu agarii, sasoa na, nèngu madhe aapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Kristus has paid in full to free us-ex from those religious regulations which are binding/tying us-ex. Previously, we-ex lived half dead (=with great trouble/effort) by shoulder.carrying the burden/weight of those religious regulations like a person who is cursed. But now the Lord Yesus has lifted that curse from us. Cuz (elaboration) it is written in the Holy Writing saying, “If a person dies from being hung on a pole, it means s/he has a bad/evil/cursed death.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kadhoe = tagantong (rope or hook)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">kadhoe = tagantong (rope or hook) ; done-done = tagantong, suspended (but UNS's laughed)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Both subject and object fronted, no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">Both subject and object fronted, no connector (asyndeton). Sudden break, going off in another direction now. Up to this point, he's almost been going around in circles talking about how we can't get free. The implicit bridge, "we can't do it," needs to be before the verse break, not after it. Putting it in Verse 12 is natural, and allows 13 to start with a bang like the Greek does. exagorazw: to redeem, to buy back, to release, to free by paying for<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>epikataratos: cursed katathema: accursed thing<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>katara: curse epi xylou: hung from any tree or wooden structure. Not specifically the cross of Christ. The Jewish idea was that if the body of an executed criminal or a murder victim were publicly exposed by hanging it from a tree or post, that would defile the land. When Roman crucifixion came along later, that was a natural extension of a much older idea.<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>LITERALLY: Christ has redeemed us from the curse of the Law, becoming a curse for us, because it has been written "Cursed is everyone who hangs on a cross,"</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lole Hari J'ara-j'ara Mamuri 21:23</note><v n="14" />Ropa Yesus Kristus madhe, sèna ka pala-bagi mamuri mi èdhi, berkat èèna ka dhu Ama Lamatua pangèd'u mi Abraham, aa hia kahèi mi suku leo. Dènge j'ara ne'e, dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu parcaya Kristus, bisa abhu Roh Ama Lamatua dhu Na jaji le.<bt>When Yesus Kristus died to save us-inc, that blessing2 which God had already given to Abraham, then came down to the other nations/tribes as well. In that way, all people who believe Kristus can recieve/get/ obtain that Spirit of God's which He has promised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: that the blessing of Abraham"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: that the blessing of Abraham might come to the Gentiles by Christ Jesus, that we may receive the promise of the Spirit through faith.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ama Lamatua kèpe pa'èra lii padhadha Na<bt>God holds tight/firmly to His promise</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Doe ne'e ja'a neo kore pakasame nèti mamuri èdhi bèli-mai bèli-mai. Ladhe abhu dhèu dhu suri sasuri lii padhadha nèti pusaka, ka dhu ènyi le ngara na ètu sasuri ne, sasoa na, sasuri ne lèke tare'a. Dhèu leo bisa boe ère eele ngaa dhu suri ètu d'ara sasuri èèna, aa bisa boe suri tabha hari ngaa-ngaa asa d'ara sasuri èèna.<bt>Siblings! Now I want to use an example from our-inc everyday lives. If there is a person who writes an inheritance letter, then s/he signs/presses his/her name on that letter, that letter is true/fixed/legal. Another person cannot cancel what is written in that letter, and cannot write adding anything else in that letter.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bèli-mai bèli-mai = sehari-hari ; ènyi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">bèli-mai bèli-mai = sehari-hari ; ènyi = tendes (jempol) ; sasuri lii padhadha = (any) surat perjanjian ; pakabèle = 1) open their hand, 2) bubarkan, 3) batal (but UNS's not get it in this context); @@ deo = tadi but doe = sekarang but deo ne'e dan doe ne'e both mean hari ini @@ ; ère eele = pull away</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="athetew: set aside, displace diatheke: last"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">athetew: set aside, displace diatheke: last will and testament, a will that has been ratified<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>epidiatassomai: add a codicil kurow: confirm, ratify, validate, put into effect, establish<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: Brothers, I speak with a human example: even a person's will, if ratified, nobody can cancel it or add to it.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Sama sèmi èèna kahèi, lod'o Ama Lamatua patari lii padhadha dènge Abraham, aa dènge ana-èpu na. Ama Lamatua peka boe, na, &lt;&lt;Ja'a patari lii padhadha ne dènge ana-èpu èu sèra&gt;&gt;, lula Na padhadha boe dènge dhèu ae-ae. Te ngaa Na padhadha dhoka dènge ana-èpu Abraham ca dhèu di, nuka Kristus.<bt>Like that also, when God bound/established a promise with Abraham and with his descendant. God did not say “I make this promise with your descendants”, because He did not promise to lots of people. But He only promised to just one descendant of Abraham, that is Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paj'ari = make (a promise; focus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">paj'ari = make (a promise; focus on initial step) [Lena not know] ; patari = start to weave a basket, establish (initial step)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now to Abraham and his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now to Abraham and his offspring the promises were made. It doesn't say, "and to your children", which are many, but to one, "and to your son", which is Christ.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Sasuri lii Yunani ètu ne'e, suri peka na, &lt;&lt;peka boe, na, &lt;patari lii padhadha ne dènge hini èu sèra (jamak)&gt;&gt;, te ngaa &lt;&lt;dènge dhoka hini èu èci di (tunggal)&gt;&gt;. Ètu lii padhadha ne, sasoa lii Yunani nèti &lt;&lt;hini&gt;&gt; ne, na, &lt;&lt;ana-èpu&gt;&gt;. Ladhe kahèi mi <span class="Italic">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka</span> 12:7.<bt>The Yunani language Bible here writes, “doesn't say ‘bind a promise with your-sg seeds (plural)’, but ‘with your seed (singular)’.” In this promise, the Yunani word “seed” means “descendant”. See also at Genesis 12:7.</bt></note><v n="17" />A'abhu ja'a sèmi ne'e ka: Ama Lamatua paj'ari uru lii padhadha dènge Abraham. Hèia èpa ngasu tèlu nguru tèu ku, heka Na papuru atora agama hia dhèu Yahudi kèna, re baki ra Musa. Te ngaa masi ka sèmi èèna, Lamatua ère heka lii padhadha dhu Na tao uru èèna.<bt>My intention is like this: God made a promise first/beforehand with Abraham. After four hundred thirty years, only then He handed down the religious regulations to the Yahudi people, through/by means of their Gf Musa. Even though it was like that, nevertheless God2 did not cancel that promise of His which He had made previously.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akurow: make void, annul, cancel katargew:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">akurow: make void, annul, cancel katargew: make ineffective<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>prokurow: ratify previously, confirm ahead of time LITERALLY: This is what I mean, that the covenant, which was ratified before by God about Christ, the Law, which was given four hundred and thirty years later, cannot cancel, to make the promise null and void.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kalua nèti Masir 12:40</note><v n="18" />Te Lamatua hia boe mèngi-nale mi Abraham, lula na tao madhutu atora ne. Te ngaa Lamatua hia berkat lula Na moa tèke le, karèi nèti uru ka, ho hia hadia mi Abraham. Èèna nuka sèmi ana ca dhèu abhu pusaka nèti ama na. Ana ne abhu pusaka na, lula ama na dhu padhadha uru le, lula boe nèti ana ne tao madhutu atora.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 did not give blessing to Abraham because he followed regulations. But God2 gave blessing2 because He had pre-promised to give a gift to Abraham from long before. That is like a child who recieves an inheritance from his father. He gets the inheritance because his father had pre-promised, not because that child acts according to regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kleronomia: inheritance xarizomai: give freely|i(18) (18)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">kleronomia: inheritance xarizomai: give freely<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: For if the inheritance be from the Law, then it is not by promise; but God gave it to Abraham by promise.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 4:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />De ja'a neo karèi sèmi ne'e: ladhe Ama Lamatua sèmi nare Abraham j'aj'i mi dhèu mola lula lalèka na, nga tao ka Lamatua tabha hari atora agama re Musa? Lamatua tabha atora agama sèra, sèna ka aj'a dhèu rai-haha lula-nèti sasala-sasigo ra. Dad'èi Na sèna ka dhèu rai-haha mamuri madhutu dad'èi atora sèra, toke ana-èpu Abraham ca dhèu mai. Hèia ladhe dhèu ne mai ka, nuka Kristus èèna, na, atora ne parluu heka.<bt>So (consequently), I want to ask like this: if God accepted Abraham as a straight/just person because of his belief, why did God2 adding further religious regulations via/by Musa? He added religious regulations to teach humans about their various wrongs. His intent/will/desire was that humans live according to the will/intent of those regulations, until that one descendant of Abraham came. Then, when that descendant came, that is the aforementioned Kristus, those regulations were no longer needed anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prostithemi: to add parabasis: to overstep,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">prostithemi: to add parabasis: to overstep, to transgress<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>diatassw: order, direct, command diatage: ordinance, direction<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>mesites: mediator, intermediary, representative, arbitrator, lawyer, LITERALLY: Why, then, the Law? It was added because of transgressions until the Child to whom the promise referred had come. The Law was handed down through angels by the hands of a mediator.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Lod'o Lamatua papuru atora agama Yahudi, Nèngu j'ole mema boe mi dhèu Yahudi sèra. Te ngaa Na hia re ana pajuu Na nèti sorga, mai pangèd'u mi adhe-aai Musa, heka Musa hia asa dhèu Yahudi kèna. Dènge j'ara ne'e, Musa j'aj'i nuka sèmi kalete sa nèti Lamatua dènge dhèu-dhèu unu Na.<bt>When God2 gave those Yahudi religious regulations, He did not hand them over directly. But He gave via His underlings from heaven (*angels), then they brought them to Musa's hand, only then did Musa give them to the Yahudi people. In that manner, Musa became like a bridge for God and His people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nèti (here) = between, antara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">nèti (here) = between, antara</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Te ngaa ropa Ama Lamatua tao lii pajaji dènge Abraham, Na pake boe kalete. Te Lamatua peka unu Na dènge Abraham! Dènge sèmi èèna, èdhi te'a, na, lii pajaji Lamatua ne kab'ua risi eele nèti atora sèra.<bt>But when God made a promise with Abraham, He did not use a bridge. Cuz (elaboration) it was He himself who spoke directly to Abraham. In that manner, we-inc know that, that promise of God2's is more valuable/important than those regulations. [EXEG: Translators Notes, Yakan BT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now, a mediator is not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now, a mediator is not a mediator of one, but God is one.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Atora agama aj'a dhèu rai-haha lula-nèti sasala-sasigo ra<bt>Religious regulations teach humans about their various kinds of wrong</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Lod'o Lamatua hia atora agama asa Musa èèna, pasala dènge lii-lii pajaji Na, do? Aad'o! Te ladhe abhu atora dhu dhèu rai-haha bisa tao madhutu ne, ho Lamatua sèmi nare ne sèna ka na bisa mamuri, tatu atora dhèu Yahudi bisa tao sèmi èèna kahèi. Madhutu iia-iia na, abhu boe atora èci sa dhu dhèu bisa tao madhutu ne, sèna ka cuhi d'ara Lamatua ho Lamatua sèmi nare ne j'aj'i mi dhèu mola.<bt>When God2 gave those religious regulations to Musa, did that oppose/be.in.contradiction.to his promises, [tag question]? Of course not! Cuz (elaboration) if there are regulations which a human can follow, in.order for God2 to accept him/her, [so that s/he can live] surely the Yahudi people's regulations could also do like.that. But in actual fact there is not a single regulation which a person can follow, to cool God2's insides, so that God2 will accept him/her as a straight/just person. [cool God's liver = make God no longer angry -- not in a bad sense but from justifiable anger.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cuhi dara na = padamkan ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">cuhi dara na = padamkan ; cuhi ai = padamkan api @@GRAMMAR the form without the prefix seems to be active and causative, whereas the form with the prefix seems to be U oriented pacuhi = cool (state)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zwopoiew: make alive LITERALLY: Is the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">zwopoiew: make alive LITERALLY: Is the Law then against the promises of God? Certainly not! For if there could have been a Law given which could have given life, surely righteousness would have been given by the Law.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Te ètu Sasuri Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci èèna, suri peka na, dhèu aa'i-aa'i ra pa'èki madhe dènge rupa-rupa sasala ra. Nèti èèna ka, dhodhoka dhèu dhu parcaya Yesus Kristus di, bisa abhu ngaa dhu Ama Lamatua moa tèke èèna.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in God2's Holy Writing it is written saying, all people are completely bound/tied.up with all.kinds.of wrongs. That's why only a person who believes Yesus Kristus, [is] the one who can recieve that which God has promised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hina: God proves that people have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">hina: God proves that people have all sinned, in order to make it clear that their deeds are inadequate and trusting him is the only recourse. sugkleiw: be enclosed, be imprisoned [see verse 24]<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>LITERALLY: But the Scripture declares that all are prisoners of sin, so that what was promised, being given through faith in Jesus Christ, might be given to those who believe.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Lod'o Kristus dhae mai mèka, ji'i dhèu Yahudi pa'èki madhe dènge atora sèra, toke bisa boe kalau. Te ngaa ropa d'ai lod'o na, Lamatua bhoke j'ara ho ji'i kalua nèti atora sèra, ladhe ji'i parcaya Kristus.<bt>When Kristus had not yet come, we-exc Yahudi people were completely bound/tied up with those regulations, to the point that we could move. But when the time arrived, God2 opened the path/way so that we-ex could be free/escape from those regulations, if we-ex believe Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalau = bergerak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">kalau = bergerak</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phrourew: be confined, be held under"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">phrourew: be confined, be held under custody be the law, be under guard sugkleiw: be enclosed, be imprisoned, keep under restraint [see v 22]<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>LITERALLY: But before faith came, we were kept under the Law, shut up unto the faith which would afterward be revealed.</Message></Annotation><v n="24-25" />De atora agama sèra, sama sèmi dhèu madhenge dhu aj'a paie-iie èdhi toke Kristus mai. Te ngaa ropa Na mai ku, heka èdhi bisa parcaya Ne, sèna ka èdhi mamuri pabe'a dènge Ama Lamatua. Nèti èèna ka, limuri ne èdhi parluu heka dhèu madhenge èèna.<bt>So (consequently), those aforementioned religious regulations, [are] for example a guardian who teaches us-inc well until Kristus come. But when He has come, then we can believe Him, so that we-inc live in a reciprocally good relationship with God. That's why now we-inc don't need that guardian anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paidagwgos: attendant, caretaker, guardian, custodian, guide,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">paidagwgos: attendant, caretaker, guardian, custodian, guide, superintendant, servant who took the children to and from school LITERALLY: So the Law was our caretaker to bring us to Christ, that we might be justified by faith.<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>LITERALLY: But faith has come, and we are no longer under a caretaker.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dhèu parcaya j'aj'i le a'ari Kristus<bt>Believers have become Kristus' family</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Limuri ne, miu j'aj'i le ana-ana Ama Lamatua, lula miu parcaya Yesus Kristus.<bt>Now you-pl have become God's children, because you believe in Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For you are all children"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For you are all children of God through faith in Christ Jesus.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Miu aa'i-aa'i mi dhu sarani èle le, ho j'aj'i dhèu unu Na dhu pa'èki madhe dènge Ne.<bt>All of you-pl who have been baptised to become His people, are also bound/tied/linked up (tight) with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="enduw: to put on, to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">enduw: to put on, to be clothed, to become like LITERALLY: For as many of you as were baptized into Christ are clothed in him.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Dhèu dhu lèka Kristus, aa'i-aa'i ra èci èèna ka, beda boe. De masi ka miu dhèu Yahudi, do dhèu Yahudi boe, ènu do ènu boe, dhèu mone do dhèu bhèni, aa'i-aa'i mi dhu pa'èki le dènge Yesus Kristus, ca ropa èèna ka.<bt>All people who believe2 in Kristus are the same, without differences. So whether you are Yahudi people, or, non Yahudi people, slaves or not slaves, male or female, all the people who are bound/tied with Yesus Kristus, are the.same (type).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èci risi boe èci ; aa'i-aa'i"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">èci risi boe èci ; aa'i-aa'i ra èci èèna ka ; èci beda boe dènge èci</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There is not Jew or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There is not Jew or Greek, neither slave or free man, neither male nor female, but you all are in [union with] Christ Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Kristus ne, ana-èpu Abraham dhu Ama Lamatua padhadha karèi nèti uru ka. Lula miu pa'èki le dènge Kristus, nèti èèna ka miu j'aj'i le tare'a-re'a ana-èpu Abraham. Dènge j'ara sèmi èèna, miu bisa kahèi abhu berkat dhu Ama Lamatua moa tèke le mi Abraham.<bt>The aforementioned Kristus, is Abraham descendant whom God promised from long ago. Because you are tied/bound to Kristus, that's why you also have become Abraham's real/true descendants. In that manner/Because of that, you also can recieve that blessing2 which God pre-promised to Abraham.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kleronomos: heir LITERALLY: If you are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">kleronomos: heir LITERALLY: If you are of Christ, then you are Abraham's children, heirs according to the promise.<span class="Italic">(29)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 4:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Ja'a pakasame dhu leo hari. Ca dhèu ana dhu dènge hak ho abhu pusaka nèti ama na, ladhe ama na madhe. Te ngaa ladhe ana ne ana iiki ae era, nèngu bisa mèka abhu pusaka èèna, masi ka èèna na aa'i-aa'i se unu nèngu. Lula nèngu d'ai mèka umur, nèngu ne nuka sèmi ènu dhu dènge boe hak, sèna ka nare mèdha-panyau lamatua na.<bt>I'll give another example. A child has the right to get/recieve an inheritance from his/her father if/when his/her father dies. But if the child is still small, s/he cannot yet recieve that aforementioned inheritance, even though it all will later become his/her possession. Because his/her age is not yet sufficient, he/she is like a slave who does not have the right to take his/her boss' belongings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ana ca dhèu vs. ca dhèu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">ana ca dhèu vs. ca dhèu ana (difference is specific/non-specific) @@ GRAMMAR</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diapherww: to differ kleronomos: heir|i(1) (1)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">diapherww: to differ kleronomos: heir<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>nepios: minor, child, not of age kurios: lord, owner<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: But I mean, as long as the heir is a child, he is no different from a slave, though he is owner of everything,</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Nèti èèna ka, hud'i dènge ku dhèu dhu pa'uri ana ne dènge pusaka na. Ana ne hud'i madhutu ku dad'èi nèti dhèu madhenge nèngu, toke d'ai lod'o dhu ama na pama'ète nare èèna, heka na sèmi nare pusaka na kèna.<bt>Because of that, there must be a person who manages the child and his/her inheritance. That child must follow that guardian's will, until the time which his/her father has decided, only then s/he may recieve [+accomplishment] that inheritance.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="around 17-18 here, or when married"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">around 17-18 here, or when married and able to support himself/herself</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epitropos: guardian, a person to whom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">epitropos: guardian, a person to whom the entire care of an underaged child is entrusted oikonomous: manager, trustee, administrator, steward<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>prothesmia: appointed time, set time LITERALLY: but he is under guardians and managers until the time set by his father.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Sèmi èèna kahèi dènge èdhi. Lod'o Yesus Kristus dhae mai mèka, èdhi nuka sèmi ana iiki èèna. Te èdhi dhu pa'èki madhe dènge dad'èi rai-haha, nuka sèmi ènu ca dhèu.<bt>It's like that also with us-inc. When Yesus Kristus had not yet come, we-inc were still like that small child. Cuz (elaboration) we-inc were still tied/bound up (tight) to the world's desires/ways of the world, like a slave.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stoixeia: fundamental principles, basic principles, elementary"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">stoixeia: fundamental principles, basic principles, elementary principles, basic spirits kosmos: world, universe<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: So also we, when we were young, we were slaves under the [fundamental / basic] [elements / spirits] of the world;</Message></Annotation><v n="4-5" />Te ngaa ropa d'ai lod'o na, Ama Lamatua pua mai Ana d'èlu Na dhu j'aj'i dhèu rai-haha èèna, sèna ka dhèu rai-haha bisa kahèi j'aj'i dhèu dhu Ama Lamatua ded'e nare j'aj'i ana-ana Na. Ana d'èlu Na èèna mamuri madhutu atora agama dhèu Yahudi, sèna ka Nèngu bisa patabuli dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu uru èèna pa'èki dènge atora se.<bt>But at the right time, God sent His own Child who became a human, so that humans also could be elevated/lifted/ adopted becoming God's children. That own Child of His, lived according to the Yahudi people's religious regulations, so that He could free all people who were previously bound/tied to those aforementioned regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ana bhala = ana tiri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">ana bhala = ana tiri</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho sèna ka dhèu rai-haha, bisa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">ho sèna ka dhèu rai-haha, bisa kahèi j'aj'i ana-ana Lamatua.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But when the right time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But when the right time came, God sent forth his Son, made from woman, made under the Law, eksagorazw: to redeem<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>apolambanw: to receive huiothesia: adoption<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: to redeem those who were under the Law, that we might receive adoption as sons.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Lula miu j'aj'i le ana-ana Ama Lamatua, nèti èèna ka Na hia le Roh Ana Na mai asa d'ara miu. Dènge j'ara ne'e, miu dènge hak paroa Ama Lamatua, na, &lt;&lt;Ama Pasue&gt;&gt;.<bt>Because you-pl have become God's children, that's why He has sent His Child's Spirit to come into your insides. In that manner/Because of that, you have the right to call God, &lt;&lt;Beloved Father/Dear Dad&gt;&gt;.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exapostellw: send out krazw: call, cry|i(6)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">exapostellw: send out krazw: call, cry<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: Because you are sons, God sent the Spirit of his Son into our hearts, crying "Abba, Father".</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />De limuri ne miu j'aj'i heka ènu dhu dènge boe hak ho abhu pusaka. Te ngaa miu j'aj'i le ana-ana Ama Lamatua dhu dènge hak, sèna ka abhu pusaka aa'i-aa'i dhu Na pajaji tèke le.<bt>So (consequently) now, you-pl are no longer slaves who do not have the right to recieve inheritance. But you have become God's children who have the right to recieve all that inheritance which His has promised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So that you are no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So that you are no longer a slave but a son. And since a son, also an heir through God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:5-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 8:15-17</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus ngee bia dènge dhèu Galati<bt>Paulus worries (=thinks heavy) about the Galatia people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Uru èèna, lod'o miu tadhe mèka Ama Lamatua, miu tao iisi mi j'aj'i ènu, ho sogo-tagu ngaa-ngaa dhu lèke boe.<bt>Previously, when you-pl did not yet know God, you made yourselves become like slaves, to traditional.worship (worship word contrasts with the worship word used in Christianity/Islam) things were are not true/right/ real.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phusis: nature LITERALLY: Formerly when you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">phusis: nature LITERALLY: Formerly when you did not know God, you were slaves to those who by nature are not gods;<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Te ngaa limuri ne, miu tadhe le Ama Lamatua. Be'a risi, ja'a peka, na, Ama Lamatua ka dhu tadhe miu. De tasamia ka miu neo lèpa hari asa sogo-tagu ngaa dhu guna boe, aa dhu dènge boe koasa ngaa-ngaa sèra? Miu neo tao iisi mi pa'èki dènge j'ara-j'ara sèra, sèna ka j'aj'i hari ènu ra, do?<bt>But now, you know God. It's better if I say that it is God who knows you-pl. So (consequently), how can it get to the point that you want to return again, to traditional.worship those things which have no use, and which have no power whatsoever? Do you want to make yourselves tied/bound with those things, to become their slaves again, [tag question]?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epistrephw: turn asthenes: sick, weak. Have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">epistrephw: turn asthenes: sick, weak. Have to change the order to put "not" at the end of the sentence so as to prevent its scope from including "junk"<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>ptwxos: begging poor, miserable stoixeia: elements, elementary principles, fundamental principles<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>anwthen: again LITERALLY: But now knowing God, or rather, being known by God, why do you turn again to those weak and beggarly [elements / spirits] which want to enslave you again?<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ja'a tadèngi, na, miu kèpe atora ho pakab'ua risi lod'o-lod'o hua iia madhutu lod'o, hèru, èj'i lai, hèru hadhu, dènge tèu, ho neo pakarej'e d'ara Ama Lamatua.<bt>I have heard that you are carrying out regulations to honour special days, according to days, months, rainy-dry seasons, and years, in.order.to try and make God's insides happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paraterew: to keep LITERALLY: You observe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">paraterew: to keep LITERALLY: You observe days and months, and seasons, and years.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ne'e ne ka dhu pa'ele iie ngangee ja'a! Mage dhoka j'aj'èra ja'a aj'a-nori miu nèbhu nare sange ne'e, ele iie d'ara di.<bt>This makes me worry! Lest my weariness/ effort/ suffering to teach you for this long, just becomes pointless.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phobew: to fear mepws: lest somehow|i(11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">phobew: to fear mepws: lest somehow<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>kopiaw: become tired LITERALLY: I fear for you, that somehow I have worked hard for you in vain.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />A'ari dhu pasue! Ja'a manèngi sèna ka miu mamuri pa'èki ia ka dènge madha j'ara sèra, sèmi ja'a ne. Te mamuri ja'a ne pa'èki heka le dènge atora agama, èci èèna ka dènge miu dhèu Yahudi boe. Uru èèna, lod'o èdhi bera-bera era, miu pasusa boe ja'a.<bt>Beloved siblings! I request that you live no longer bound to those things, like me here. Cuz (elaboration) I live no longer bound to those religious regulations, the same as you who are non Yahudi. Previously, when we-inc were still together, I never received any trouble/difficulty from you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deomai: to ask adikew: to do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">deomai: to ask adikew: to do wrong, to wrong someone<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: I beg you, brothers, be as I am, because I became like you. You have not done wrong to me;</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Miu aa'i-aa'i mi me'a, na, ca hari ni, lod'o ja'a mai hiu-hiu èèna, ho peka-padhai Lii Lolo Be'a dènge miu, ngi'u aae ja'a ne roe-bhilu.<bt>You all know that, that prior time, when I came the first time to tell that Good News to you, my body was weak (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="roe-bhilu = sangat cape, sangat lelah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">roe-bhilu = sangat cape, sangat lelah ; bhilu (not known)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="astheneia: weakness, illness, sickness LITERALLY: You"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">astheneia: weakness, illness, sickness LITERALLY: You know that because of weakness/sickness of the flesh/body I preached to you the first time.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Masi ka sèmi èèna, te ngaa miu tule eele boe ja'a, lula miu sèmi mere ja'a nuka sèmi ana pajuu Ama Lamatua nèti sorga. Risi-risi hari, miu sèmi mere ja'a ne, nuka sèmi Yesus Kristus mesa Na.<bt>Nevertheless, you did not reject me, because you recieved me, just like I here, [was] God's underling from heaven (=angel). Even more, you recieved me, just like I here, [was] Yesus Kristus himself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peirasmos: trial, test eksouthenew: despise, scorn,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">peirasmos: trial, test eksouthenew: despise, scorn, disdain someone<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>ekptuw: despise, disdain, reject, loath, spit out dexomai: receive, welcome<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: and even though my physical condition was a trial for you, you did not despise or reject me, but you received me as an angel of God, as Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Lod'o èèna, èdhi aa'i-aa'i ti karej'e titu kèna. Te ngaa, nga tao ka limuri ne, sèmi heka èèna? Uru èèna, miu sue ja'a titu kèna, ka miu toke neo ed'o eele ana madha miu ho hia ja'a.<bt>At that time, we-inc all together were very happy. But, why is it no longer like that now? At that previous time you loved me very much, to.the point that you would have been willing to gouge out your own eye/s to give to me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lii Dhao: ère eele adhe-usu mi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">Lii Dhao: ère eele adhe-usu mi hia ja'a ; ere eele = tarik kasi kaluar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makarismos: joy, happiness, blessing, satisfaction. NOT"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">makarismos: joy, happiness, blessing, satisfaction. NOT "get plenny aloha fo me" marturew: bear witness, testify<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>exorussw: tear out, pluck out, pull out LITERALLY: Then where did your joy go? For I testify about you, that if possible, you would have plucked out your eyes and given them to me.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Te ngaa limuri ne, miu ngee, na, ja'a j'aj'i le musu miu, lula ja'a padhai dhu mola dènge miu, do?<bt>But now do you think I have become your enemy, because I speak that which true to you, [tag question]?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aletheuw: be truthful exthros: the enemy|i(16)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">aletheuw: be truthful exthros: the enemy<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: Have I now become your enemy, because I tell you the truth?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Dhèu kapod'e-kabèli sèra, ro'o boe ja'a pa'angalai dènge miu, ka ra dadugu miu ho madhutu aa'i atora agama Yahudi. Dad'èi d'ara ra, sèna ka miu bhute madhutu dad'èi rèngu di.<bt>Those habitual decievers do not want me to be friends with you, so they tempt/coax you to follow all the Yahudi people's religious regulations. They want for you to be busy-bodied following just their desires/ wishes/ways. [CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zelow: be zealous, be concerned for,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">zelow: be zealous, be concerned for, work hard for, to try to win someone's favor kalws: for good, for a good purpose<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>ekkleiw: exclude, shut out LITERALLY: They are zealous for you, but not for a good purpose. They desire to exclude you, that you may be zealous for them.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te ngaa ladhe miu maj'èni tao j'ara dhu be'a, èèna be'a kahèi! Masi ka ja'a sama-sama dènge miu, do aad'o, ngaa-ngaa tao boe. Sad'i miu tao j'ara dhu be'a.<bt>But if you are diligent to do good things, that is also good/ok! Regardless of whether I am together with you, or not, it doesn't matter. As long as you do what is good (anyway).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It is good to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It is good to be zealous always, if the purpose is good, and not only when I am with you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ana-ana pasue! Ne'e ne, ja'a sab'a bia risi hari hia miu, nuka sèmi bhèni dhu kabake pèd'a neo nara iisi. Te ja'a ae kora boe ciki sa nèti sasab'a, toke d'ara miu èci èèna ka dènge d'ara Kristus.<bt>Beloved children! Now, I work even harder for you/on your behalf, like a woman in stomach pain about to give birth. Cuz (elaboration) I do not stop working, until your insides have become the same as Kristus' insides.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kabake = perut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">kabake = perut</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wdinw: suffer birth pangs, experience childbirth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">wdinw: suffer birth pangs, experience childbirth pains mexri: until<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>morphow: to form LITERALLY: My little children, again I experience the pains of childbirth for you, until Christ is formed in you;<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Te ngaa limuri ne, ja'a ke'a heka neo tao miu tasamia hari! Ja'a d'èi titu kèna, dhiu padhai lii patoo madha dènge miu, sèna ka ja'a baku padhai lii taka sèmi ne'e ne.<bt>But now, I no longer know what to do with you! I long to go speak directly with you, so that I don't need to speak harshly like this.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thelw: to wish pareimi: to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">thelw: to wish pareimi: to be present<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>allassw: change phwne: voice, sound, tone<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>aporew: be uncertain, doubt, be perplexed, be unsure LITERALLY: I wish to be present with you now, and change my tone, because I am uncertain about you.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus pasoro lii lolo ana Hagar dènge ana Sara<bt>Paulus gives an example of the story (about) Hagar's child, and Sara's child</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ladhe miu neo mamuri madhutu atora agama dhèu Yahudi, be'a risi miu me'a uuru ku dad'èi nèti atora sèra.<bt>If you-pl want to live according to the Yahudi people's religious regulations, it's best if you first understand the intent of those regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasoro = mencocokkan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">pasoro = mencocokkan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Tell me, you who desire"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Tell me, you who desire to be under the Law, do you not hear the Law?</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua abhu lii lolo dhu lole, peka na, ana mone Abraham, dhèu dua. Nèngu abhu ana ca dhèu nèti bhèni dhu ènu na, aa ca dhèu hari nèti dhèu èmu-kamali na, dhu ènu boe.<bt>In God2's Holy Writings there is a story that says Abraham had two male children. He got one child from his slave, and the other one from his wife, who was not a slave.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paidiske: maid, female servant eleutheros: free|i(22)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">paidiske: maid, female servant eleutheros: free<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>LITERALLY: For it has been written that Abraham had two sons, one from the female slave and one from the free woman.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 16:15, 21:2</note><v n="23" />Ènu ne nara iisi ana na, lula madhutu dad'èi dhèu rai-haha. Te ngaa dhèu èmu Abraham nara iisi ana na, lula madhutu lii moa dhu Ama Lamatua peka mema le.<bt>That slave, gave birth to her child, because it was according to human desires. But Abraham's wife gave birth to her child, because it was according to the promise that God had spoken to Abraham beforehand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the one from the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the one from the slave woman was born according to the flesh, but the one from the free woman through promise.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Bhèni dhèu dua se, nuka sèmi tadha dhu pad'elo dua lii pajaji dhu Ama Lamatua padhadha dènge dhèu rai-haha. Lii pajaji èci, Lamatua pangèd'u mi Musa ètu ledhe Sinai, lod'o Nèngu papuru atora agama dhèu Yahudi. Dhèu dhu pa'èki dènge atora agama sèra, rèngu j'aj'i ènu sama sèmi Hagar kahèi.<bt>Those two aforementioned women, are like a sign to show two promises which God made with humans. The one promise God2 made with Musa at Sinai mountain, when He handed down the Yahudi people's religious regulations. People who are tied/bound to those religious regulations, they are also slaves like Hagar.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="allegorew: to speak allegorically, to tell"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">allegorew: to speak allegorically, to tell a parable, to speak figuratively diatheke: covenant, agreement, will and testament<span class="Italic">(24) (24) </span>douleia: slavery LITERALLY: Which, to speak allegorically, the women represent two agreements. One is from Mt. Sinai, giving birth to slavery, which is Hagar.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Era ètu ledhe Sinai ètu rae Arab èèna, nuka sèmi Hagar ne kahèi. Dhèu Yerusalem aa'i-aa'i lod'o limuri ne, dhu pa'èki era dènge atora agama Yahudi, rèngu sèra ènu kahèi nuka sèmi Hagar.<bt>That place on Sinai mountain in that Arab land, is also like Hagar. All the Yerusalem people now who are still tied to those Yahudi religious regulations, they also are slaves like Hagar.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sustoixew: to correspond to LITERALLY: For"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">sustoixew: to correspond to LITERALLY: For Hagar is Mt. Sinai in Arabia, corresponding to present-day Jerusalem, and is in slavery with her children.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Te ngaa lii pajaji dhu leo hari, paj'uj'u asa kota Yerusalem dhu leo èci ètu sorga. Ana-ana unu Ama Lamatua dhu pea ètu èèna, ènu boe. Te rèngu dhèu bebas dhu pa'èki boe dènge atora agama èèna. Nèti èèna ka, rèngu se èci èèna ka dènge ina ji'i Sara, dhèu èmu Abraham.<bt>But that other promise, shows/designates another Yerusalem city in heaven. God's children who live there, are not slaves. Cuz (elaboration) they are free people who are not bound/tied to those religious regulations. That's why they are like our-ex mama Sara, that wife of Abraham.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leko-leo = lain dari yg lain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">leko-leo = lain dari yg lain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the Jerusalem from above"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the Jerusalem from above is free, which is our mother;</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci, dhu suri tèke, peka na,<bt>In the Holy Writings it is written, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Wee! Bhèni dhu nara iisi nèdhi boe!<bt>“Wee! Woman who has never given birth!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nara iisi nèdhi boe = never"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">nara iisi nèdhi boe = never</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Pakarej'e d'ara mu!<bt>Make your insides happy!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Wee! Bhèni dhu rasa nèdhi boe kabake pèd'a nara iisi!<bt>Wee! Woman who has never felt stomach pain bearing children!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sod'a pakarej'e d'ara mu!<bt>Sing with joyful insides!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bhèni dhu d'ara roe-bhilu, lula dhèu èmu na pusi-pahae heka ne,<bt>The woman whose insides are shattered/distrought, because her husband no longer pays attention to her anymore,</bt><note reference="4:27" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dhèu bhèni dhu d'ara na susa lula dhèu èmu na dhu pahae heka ne, nuka Sara. Te Abraham la'e leo dènge Hagar ho abhu kolo.<bt>That woman whose insides were troubled because her husband no longer paid attention to her, that is Sara. Cuz (elaboration) Abraham went and took Hagar in order to get a child/descendant (lit. tip).</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">pe na abhu ana ae risi nèti bhèni dhu dènge dhèu èmu-kamali.&gt;&gt;<bt>later she will get/have more children than the woman who has a husband.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="euphraivw: to be glad, to rejoice"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">euphraivw: to be glad, to rejoice steira: barren<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>tiktw: to give birth hregnumi: to tear, break loose, break out<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>boaw: to shout wdinw: to suffer the pains of childbirth<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>eremos: desolate, barren LITERALLY: For it has been written, "Rejoice, barren one who has not given birth, break loose and shout, one who has not had childbirth pains, because many more are the children of the deserted one, than of her who has a husband."<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 54:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />De a'ari aa'i-aa'i! Uru èèna Ama Lamatua dhu padhadha le hia ana mi Abraham. Te ngaa nèbhu ku, heka Lamatua tao madhutu lii pajaji Na kèna, hèia Sara nara iisi Isak hia Abraham. Èdhi sama sèmi Isak kahèi, lula Ama Lamatua pajaji hia Abraham ana-èpu dhu leo kahèi.<bt>So (consequently), siblings! Previously God promised to give a child to Abraham. But it was a long time before God2 fulfilled His promise, then Sara gave birth to Isak for Abraham. We-inc are also like Isak, because God also promised to give other descendants to Abraham.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="matana = give birth 1) associated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">matana = give birth 1) associated with animals, or 2) with human fathers ‘beget’ ; kai-beko heka = tidak terikat lagi (5 UNS not know)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you brothers, you are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you brothers, you are children of promise like Isaac.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Lod'o èèna, ana ènu dhu j'aj'i madhutu dad'èi dhèu rai-haha èèna, ropa na kapai, na paj'èra Isak, dhu j'aj'i madhutu dad'èi Roh Lamatua. Èèna sama kahèi dènge ngaa dhu j'aj'i limuri ne.<bt>At that time, the slave child who was born according to human will, when he was grown, he tormented Isak who was born according to God2's Spirit's will. That also is like what happens now.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: At that time the one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: At that time the one who was born according to the flesh persecuted the one [born] according to the Spirit, thus it is now.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 21:9</note><v n="30" />Sasuri Mola-Mèci Lamatua suri kahèi, peka na, &lt;&lt;Babège eele ènu dènge ana na. Te ana nèti ènu ne dènge boe hak ho abhu pusaka. Dhodhoka ana nèti dhèu èmu kab'i na dhu dènge hak.&gt;&gt;<bt>God2's Holy Writings write, saying, “Expel/throw out that slave and her child. Cuz (elaboration) the slave child does not have the right to recieve inheritance. Only just the (legally wedded) wife's child who has the right.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But what does the Scripture"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But what does the Scripture say? "Throw out the slave woman and her son, for the son of the slave woman will not inherit with the son of the free woman."</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Lolo dhu Uru Tèka 21:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />De sèmi ne'e a'ari aa'i-aa'i! Èdhi sama boe dènge ana nèti ènu, lula èdhi pa'èki heka dènge atora agama dhèu Yahudi. Te èdhi nuka sèmi ana nèti dhèu èmu kab'i Abraham, lula èdhi parcaya Yesus Kristus.<bt>So (consequently) it's like this, siblings! We-inc here are not like the slave's child, because we-inc are no longer tied/bound anymore with the Yahudi people's religious regulations. Cuz (elaboration) we here are like the child from Abraham's legal wife, because we believe in Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, brothers, we are not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, brothers, we are not children of the slave women, but of the free woman.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus hia le èdhi bebas<bt>Kristus has (already) freed us</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Uru èèna dhèu Yahudi j'èra bia pasae atora agama ra. Te ngaa limuri ne, Kristus ded'e eele le babia èèna nèti dhèu dhu parcaya Ne. Nèti èèna ka, limuri ne èdhi pasae heka babia. De miu baku lèke kapod'e-kabèli, ho pasae hari atora sèra, tao nuka sèmi ènu sa!<bt>Previously, the Yahudi people suffered heavily shoulder.carrying their religious regulations. But now Kristus has lifted that burden/weight from people who believe in Him. That's why, now we-inc no longer carry that burden. So (consequently), don't you-pl be decieved into shoulder.carrying those regulations again, acting like a slave.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ag'o = tipu (4 UNS not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">ag'o = tipu (4 UNS not know)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />De nanene, ee! Ja'a ne, Paulus, ka dhu peka lii ne'e. Ladhe miu suna ho madhutu atora agama dhèu Yahudi, na, mamadhe Kristus dhu hia miu bebas èèna, gaguna na aad'o!<bt>So (consequently), listen! This is me, Paulus, who [is] speaking here. If you get circumcised in.order.to follow the Yahudi people's regulations, that death of Kristus which made you free (loan), has no value/worth!</bt><v n="3" />Ladhe dhèu suna ho madhutu atora agama sèmi èèna, nèngu hud'i pasae hari ku atora sèra aa'i-aa'i ra. Miu sanèd'e era, do aad'o? Te uru èèna, ja'a dhu peka mema le.<bt>If a person is circumcised to follow religious regs like that, s/he must shoulder.carry again all of those regulations. Do you still remember, or not? Cuz (elaboration) previously, I have already told you that.</bt><v n="4" />Dhèu dhu neo pake atora, sèna ka Ama Lamatua sèmi nare ne j'aj'i mi dhèu mola, nèngu tao iisi na pakaj'èu nèti Kristus. Te dènge j'ara ne'e, nèngu core eele d'ara hua iia Ama Lamatua.<bt>A person who wants to use regulations so that God will accept him/her as a straight/just person, s/he makes him/herself distanced from Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) by doing that, s/he has rejected God's goodness/grace/kindness/generosity.</bt><v n="5" />Te ngaa Roh Lamatua dhu Mola-Mèci ka dhu bhoke j'ara hia èdhi, ho èdhi parcaya Yesus Kristus. Nèti èèna ka èdhi sanao, bèli-camèd'a Ama Lamatua pama'ète, na, èdhi dhèu mola.<bt>But God's HS is the one who opens the way for us-inc so we (can) believe in Yesus Kristus. That is why we hope, that later God will decide that we are straight/righteous/just people.</bt><v n="6" />Masi ka dhèu suna, do aad'o, ngaa-ngaa tao boe. Te ngaa dhu hua iia risi, nuka dhèu dhu parcaya Kristus aa sue dhèu leo.<bt>Whether a person is circumcised or not, that is not important. But what is more/most important is that people believe in Kristus, and love other people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kolo-karisi = beda, kelebihan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">kolo-karisi = beda, kelebihan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Uru èèna, miu mamuri le madhutu j'ara dhu lèke. Te ngaa limuri ne, dhèu cee ka dhu kapod'e-kabèli miu, ka miu madhutu heka j'ara èèna?<bt>Previously, you-pl lived following the path that is true/right/appropriate. But now, who is it that has deceived (doublet) you, to the point that you don't follow that path anymore?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kapod'e-dod'e = kapod'e-kabèli (but more taputar-taputar)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">kapod'e-dod'e = kapod'e-kabèli (but more taputar-taputar)</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te a'aj'a-nanori kapod'e-kabèli dhu miu nanene èèna, mai boe nèti Ama Lamatua. Madhutu iia-iia na, Nèngu ka dhu paroa nare miu ho j'aj'i dhèu unu Na.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) that deceptive teaching which you have heard, doesn't come from God. In fact, He is the one who called you-pl to become His people.</bt><v n="9" />Ngaa dhu ra aj'a, hiu-hiu èèna dhoka ca hèb'a-dua hèb'a di. Te ngaa nèbhu-nèbhu, lii a'aj'a ne tao ngangee miu ele iie. Nuka sèmi ragi ciki dhu dhèu pakihu dènge tarigu ho neo tao roti. Nèbhu-nèbhu hèia ragi ne'e ka paca'e tarigu dhu pakihu èèna.<bt>That which they teach, orginally was just one or two words. But eventually that teaching has destroyed/ruined your thinking. Just like a little bit of yeast which a person mixed with flour to make bread. Eventually then that yeast makes all that aforementioned dough raise.</bt><note reference="5:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 5:6</note><v n="10" />Lula èdhi j'aj'i le èci dènge Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, nèti èèna ka ja'a ke'a mèu, Nèngu èèna hia miu parcaya hari mi ngaa dhu ja'a nori le sèra. Aa Ama Lamatua mesa Na, pe huku dhèu cee dhu pa'ele iie lalèka miu.<bt>Because we-inc have become one/united with Yesus Kristus, our-inc Head, that's why I clearly know/understand, that He will make you-pl believe again in what I already taught. And God himself will judge/punish whoever it is who has destroyed your faith. [Translator's Handbook/BIS]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sèmi ne'e a'ari! Ladhe ja'a aj'a, peka na, dhèu hud'i suna ku, tatu ja'a abhu boe j'aj'èra sèmi ne'e ne. Aa dhèu Yahudi tule eele boe a'aj'a ja'a lula-nèti mamadhe Yesus ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha.<bt>It's like this siblings! If I teach that people must be circumcised, surely I won't be mistreated/abused anymore like I am now. And the Yahudi people won't reject anymore my teaching about Yesus' death on the cross.</bt><v n="12" />Te ngaa dhèu dhu kapod'e-kabèli miu sèra lula j'ara suna, na soro tèke si sèna ka rèngu unu ra pake tud'i ho ari eele mèdha nèti isi ra!<bt>But those people who have deceived you about circumcision, let them go and have the knife cut off/castrate the thing from their own body (euphemism)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ari = kebirikan (animals) [Lena not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">ari = kebirikan (animals) [Lena not know, UNS knew; some not know] ; mèdha is sometimes used euphemistically for male genitals</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Lamatua patabuli le miu, ho miu mamuri pa'èki heka dènge dad'èi atora agama. Te ngaa mage pangee, na, miu bisa tao leli ho mamuri madhutu dad'èi miu di! Te dhu lèke, nuka miu hud'i mamuri pasue ku, aa paladha-leru èci dènge èci, sèmi ènu lalau-lalo'o lamatua na.<bt>Siblings! God2 has freed you-pl, so that you don't need to live bound anymore to the way/will of those religious regulations. But don't think that, you can do anything/thoughtlessly to live according to your own will! Cuz (elaboration) what's true, is that you must live loving each other, and you must serve/take.care.of each other, like a slave serves/takes.care.of his master.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tao leli = bekin sembarangan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">tao leli = bekin sembarangan</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ètu Sasuri Mola-Mèci, peka na, &lt;&lt;Èu hud'i sue ku dhèu leo, sama sèmi èu sue ngi'u èu unu mu.&gt;&gt; Ladhe miu tao madhutu dhoka atora sasue ne di, na, miu tao aa'i le madhutu dad'èi atora agama dhèu Yahudi.<bt>In God's Holy Writing it says, &lt;&lt;You-sg must love other people, the same as you love your own self.&gt;&gt; If you-pl only follow just this one regulation of love, well, you-pl have followed the intent of all the Yahudi people's regulations.</bt><note reference="5:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Atora nèti Ama-ama Agama 19:18</note><v n="15" />Te ngaa ladhe miu èci patao-palaha dènge èci, do, èci pakèji dènge èci, pe mèdhi unu mi! Nèbhu boe, te miu palaho ngi'u miu unu mi.<bt>But if you argue/be.at.odds with each other, or, you are yanking/pulling (fighting words) each other, just watch out. Not much longer, and you-pl will have destroyed yourselves.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pakèji = 1) baku mencubit dengan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">pakèji = 1) baku mencubit dengan tekanan yg keras; 2) saling menjatuhkan, memalukan, melukai perasaan, menghina</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mamuri madhutu dad'èi dhèu rai-haha, do, madhutu dad'èi Roh Mola-Mèci<bt>Live according to the will of humans, or according to the will of the Holy Spirit?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Madhutu a'abhu ja'a sèmi ne'e ka: ladhe miu mamuri madhutu dad'èi Roh Lamatua, miu madhutu heka dad'èi dhèu rai-haha.<bt>My intent/opinion is like this: if you live according to will of God's Spirit, you-pl don't follow/obey the will of human/s anymore.</bt><v n="17" />Te dad'èi dhèu rai-haha madhutu boe dad'èi Roh. Aa dad'èi Roh madhutu boe dad'èi dhèu rai-haha. Dua ra bisa boe pa'èci, te ngaa palab'a taruu! Nèti èèna ka, miu bisa heka tao hari madhutu dad'èi d'ara mi!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the will of human/s does not follow the will of the Spirit. And the will of the Spirit does not follow the will of human/s. The two cannot be united, but are in opposition continually! That's why you-pl may no longer act just according to your-pl own wills. [Translators Notes]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paguru-gete = saling menggerutu, bertengkar (ke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">paguru-gete = saling menggerutu, bertengkar (ke anjing deng anjing)</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 7:15-23</note><v n="18" />Te ngaa ladhe Roh Lamatua ator miu, na, miu pa'èki heka dènge atora sèra.<bt>But if God's Spirit is leading/managing/controlling you-pl, na, you are no longer tied/bound to those regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="na = verbal comma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">na = verbal comma</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dhèu dhu loe boe madhutu dad'èi dhèu rai-haha, nuka sèmi: dhèu dhu ad'u-ue j'ara karehe dènge dhèu dhu j'aj'i boe dhèu èmu-kamali na, dhèu dhu ngangee kaj'alu, dhu re'a boe d'ara makae,<bt>Those people who don't cease to follow/obey the will of humans, [are] for like: people who do evil with a person who is not his/her spouse (euphemism), people who have dirty thinking, who have no shame,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="re'a boe makae dara = tidak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">re'a boe makae dara = tidak tahu malu hati (lebih keras) [L. Lusi and others said makae dara is Sabu, whereas dara makae is Dhao</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />dhu sogo-tagu nidhu ho suagi dhèu, dhu pamusu, dhu d'èi pasibha d'ara lii, dhu tèka d'ara, dhu nasa leli, dhu ngee dhoka ngi'u na, dhu d'èi kakèj'i dhèu, dhu d'èi tao maruru,<bt>who traditional.worship evil spirits or do sorcery, who are enemies with each other, who quarrel/squabble, who have jealous/vengeful livers, who habitually get angry without cause/thoughtlessly, who only think of themselves, who habitually poke/incite other people, who habitually make chaos,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasibha dara lii = saling membantah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">pasibha dara lii = saling membantah (lit. juggle (rocks)) ; sibhe = catch (a rock or ball that has been tossed to you) ; kakèji = tusu-tusu</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />dhu d'èi boe dhèu leo risi ne, dhu d'èi mahu paa-paa, dhu d'èi madhutu pesta toke re'a heka makae, aa d'èi tao sasala dhu leo hari. Uru èèna, dhu ja'a pasanèd'e le, na, dhèu dhu tema tao j'ara-j'ara sèmi sèra, rèngu bisa boe j'aj'i dhèu unu Ama Lamatua.<bt>who don't like others to be/have more than them, who habitually get heavy drunk, those who participate in shameless parties, and like to do other wrongs. Previously I have reminded you, that people who normally/often/habitually do things like that, they cannot become God's people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Te ngaa dhèu dhu mamuri madhutu dad'èi Roh Lamatua, èèna na Roh tao ne ho j'aj'i dhèu dhu d'èi pasue, d'ara dhu karej'e-karae, dhu d'èi padame, taha nare d'ara, d'ara be'a dènge dhèu leo, dhu d'èi soru-bara dhèu, dhu d'èi kèpe pa'èra-èra lii pajaji,<bt>But a person who lives according the will of God's Spirit, that Spirit will make him/her become a person who habitually loves, whose insides are happy-joyful (doublet), who habitually lives in peaceful relationships, who is patient, who has is good/generous/kind toward other people; who habitually helps (doublet) other people, who habitually holds.on.to/fulfills his/her promises, [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk has two senses ‘generous’ and ‘goodness’ (NLT, CEV, LN), check that your term includes the ‘generous’ sense. NRSV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dara dhu taleo moro-moro = luas,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">dara dhu taleo moro-moro = luas, legah, tidak ada beban (receptive, open towards ideas, people)</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />dhu lii mako dènge dhèu aa'i-aa'i, aa bisa j'aga paie-iie mamuri na. Abhu boe atora èci sa dhu magee j'ara se'e se.<bt>who is kind/polite to all people, and who can guard/control him/herself well. There is not a single regulation, which forbids these things. [NOTE to daughter translations: check that “jaga diri” isn't too broad.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rèhu mare = senyum ; lii"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">rèhu mare = senyum ; lii mako = berbicara dgn lemah-lembut ; bhabhae = halangi</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="praytees: gentleness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">praytees: gentleness</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Dhèu dhu j'aj'i le dhèu unu Yesus Kristus, nèngu dhu pakaj'èu le nèti dad'èi dhèu rai-haha. Te d'ara dhu d'èi tao bhelu èèna, dhu na paku pamadhe le ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha palere-lere dènge Yesus.<bt>A person who has entered to become Yesus Kristus' person, s/he has distanced/separated himself from the will of human/s. Cuz (elaboration) those desires to do evil, s/he has nailed dead (=totally nailed down) on the cross together with Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dadèi dara dhu neo tao bhelu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">dadèi dara dhu neo tao bhelu èèna</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />De ladhe Roh Lamatua hia le mamuri hiu mi èdhi, na, èdhi hud'i madhutu taruu ku dad'èi Nèngu.<bt>So (consequently), if God's Spirit has given new life to us-inc, we-inc must continually follow/obey His will.</bt><v n="26" />Nèti èèna ka, baku padedha iisi, baku d'èi èci kakèj'i èci, aa baku patèka d'ara èci dènge èci.<bt>That's why we-inc we don't elevate ourselves, [we] don't habitually incite/provoke each other, and [we] aren't jealous/vengeful with each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koa iisi = puji diri ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">koa iisi = puji diri ; koa-kadiri = puji dan menghormati ; kuri-kuri = kira-kira ; dara paneo = hati yg a keterikatan batin</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Èci soru-bara èci<bt>Helping each other</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Ladhe abhu dhèu parcaya ca dhèu dhu tao sala, na, miu dhu me'a tare'a-re'a dad'èi Roh Lamatua, lami padhai lii mako-mako dènge ne dènge d'ara mola. Hèia mèti hari ne, sèna ka madhutu j'ara dhu lèke nèti Lamatua. Te ngaa j'aga ngi'u mi, sèna ka baku manahu asa sasala na èèna.<bt>Siblings! If there is a believer who does wrong, you-pl who truly know (personal knowledge, not head knowledge) God's Spirit's will/ways, go speak kindly/nicely with him/her with straight insides. Then bring him/her back, so.that s/he follows God2's path which is true/appropriate. But watch yourselves, lest you fall (moral/social) into that wrong of his/hers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katartizw: restore, put in order, restore"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">katartizw: restore, put in order, restore to former condition, make right, correct in order to restore paraptwma: trespass, transgression, false step, offense<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>peirazw: tempt, try, test, enticement to sin pneumatikos: spiritual, living by the Spirit<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>prautes: humility, meekness, gentleness, the opposite of arrogance or harshness prolambanw: overtake, detect, surprise someone<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>skopew: notice, consider, paying attention, be careful LITERALLY: Brothers, if a person is detected in some sin, you who are spiritual, restore the person in a spirit of gentleness, paying attention to yourself, so that you will not be tempted.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ladhe dhèu paraga dènge sasusa, na, miu dhu leo lami soru-bara ne. Te dènge sèmi èèna, miu tao le madhutu atora nèti Kristus.<bt>If a person encounters/experiences trouble/difficulty, you-pl others help (doublet) him/her. Cuz (elaboration) by doing that you act according to Kristus' regulation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anaplerow make complete, fulfill, satisfy the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">anaplerow make complete, fulfill, satisfy the requirements of baros: weight, burden, load, heavy load<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>bastaxw: carry, bear LITERALLY: Bear each others' burdens, an so fulfill the law of Christ.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ladhe abhu dhèu padedha iisi, peka na, nèngu risi nèti dhèu leo, aa te ngaa aad'o sèmi èèna, na, nèngu tipu ngi'u nèngu unu na.<bt>If a person lifts him/herself up saying s/he is more/better than other people, when in actual fact it's not like that, s/he is decieving him/herself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phrenapataw: to deceive LITERALLY: For if"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">phrenapataw: to deceive LITERALLY: For if a person thinks he is something, when he is nothing, he deceives himself.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />De ca dhèu-dhèu ka hud'i parisa ku ngaa dhu nèngu ad'u-ue. Ladhe ngaa dhu nèngu tao ne be'a le, pe ne'a unu na. Mage pasèku dènge tatao dhèu leo.<bt>So (consequently), each person must examine that which s/he does (doublet). If that which s/he does is good, then s/he knows that for him/herself. Don't compare around with other people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ca dhèu-dhèu = each person ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">ca dhèu-dhèu = each person ; roca = 1) bosan, 2) puas'; padai-delu = compare, banding [Laz Aplugi &amp; Helena not know] ; pasèku = babanding</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dokimazw: examine, test kauxema: boast|i(4) (4)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">dokimazw: examine, test kauxema: boast<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: But let each person examine his own actions, and then he will have reason to boast because of himself alone, and not because of another.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ja'a peka sèmi èèna, lula ca dhèu-dhèu ka dhu tago nare unu na, ngaa dhu nèngu tao.<bt>I speak like that, because each person must be responsible him/her self for that which s/he does.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phortion: load, normal duty LITERALLY: For"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">phortion: load, normal duty LITERALLY: For each person should carry his own load.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Te ngaa dhèu dhu sèmi nare le lii holo-nori Lamatua, nèngu hud'i pabagi ku rui-j'aj'èra na, ho soru-bara dhèu dhu aj'a-nori nèngu.<bt>But a person who accepts God2's teaching/words/ advice, s/he must divide the results of his/her work, to help (doublet) the person/s who have taught him/her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koinwnew: share, give someone a share"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">koinwnew: share, give someone a share of something, give material things, participate katexew: teach<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: But let the one who is being taught the word share every good thing with the one who teaches.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Sanèd'e, ee! Ama Lamatua ne'a aa'i mèu-mèu. De baku tipu ngi'u miu unu mi, aa baku neo tipu Lamatua. Lula, ngaa dhu dhèu sèle ètu d'ara oka-tedhe, pe nèngu abhu hari hua-hela na.<bt>Remember, ee! God knows everything. So (consequently), don't deceive yourselves, and don't try to deceive God2. Because what a person plants in a garden (doublet), later he will get back that harvest/result (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="therizw: reap, harvest mukterizw: treat with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">therizw: reap, harvest mukterizw: treat with contempt, mock, make a fool of<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>planaw: deceive, be mistaken speirw: sow, plant<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: Do not be deceived, God is not mocked. Whatever a person plants, that he will harvest.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Sèmi èèna kahèi, ladhe dhèu ad'u-ue j'ara bhelu-katub'a madhutu dad'èi na, pe na dui nare hari mamuri dhu ele iie. Te ngaa ladhe dhèu tao j'ara be'a madhutu dad'èi Roh Mola-Mèci, pe nèngu abhu hari mamuri dhu lèke toke d'ai mia-mia.<bt>It's like that also, if a person does evil (doublet) things according to his/her will, later s/he will get back a destroyed/ruined life. But if a person does good things according to the Holy Spirit's will, later that person will get back true/just/right life which does not stop. [EXEG: Bruce, on "corruption" = "indulgence in such things would have disastrous results in their personal and corporate lives alike."]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="madhii-manèro = umur panjang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">madhii-manèro = umur panjang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="therizw reap, harvest phthora: ruin|i(8) (8)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">therizw reap, harvest phthora: ruin<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>speirw: sow, plant LITERALLY: Because he who plants for the sinful nature harvests destruction from the sinful nature, but he who plants for the Spirit, from the Spirit harvests eternal life.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Nèti èèna ka, miu baku roca tao j'ara dhu be'a. Te ropa d'ai lod'o na, èdhi abhu hari j'ara dhu be'a, sad'i èdhi taha taruu.<bt>Because of that, you-pl should not get bored/disinterested in doing good things. Cuz (elaboration) in its time, we-inc will also get back good things, as long as we-inc continually endure.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="egkakew: become weary, get tired ekluw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">egkakew: become weary, get tired ekluw: become weary, get slack, give up, become discouraged<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: Let us not get tired in doing good, because in due time we will reap/receive if we do not give up.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />De ropa èdhi abhu lod'o dhu taleo, na, èdhi tao mema ka j'ara-j'ara dhu be'a hia mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i ra, risi-risi mi a'ari èdhi dhèu parcaya sèra.<bt>So (consequently), when we-inc have opportunity, we should go ahead and do good things for all people, and especially for our believing siblings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE: ladhe èdhi abhu lod'o dhu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">NOTE: ladhe èdhi abhu lod'o dhu taleo, is ambiguous in the same way the Gk is. 1) if we are presented with or encounter an opportunity to do good, take it; 2) if we have time (in the midst of our busy-ness)...</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, as often as we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, as often as we have the chance, let us do good to everyone, but especially to the family of believers.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus pa'èle sasuri na<bt>Paulus closes his letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sasuri ne'e, ja'a ka suri unu ku, pake huruf dhu kapai aae hua.<bt>Now it's I myself who am writing, using big letters.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Look what big letters I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Look what big letters I write with my own hand!</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Sanèd'e, ee! Dhèu kapod'e-kabèli sèra lèka kahèi mi Yesus Kristus dhu madhe ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha. Te ngaa rèngu laka-seti miu ho suna, lula ra madha'u dènge dhèu Yahudi leo, rèngu mage dhèu se paj'èra si, ladhe rèngu aj'a, peka na, Ama Lamatua sèmi nare kahèi dhèu dhu madhutu boe atora suna. Nèti èèna ka, rèngu se d'èi solo-mako dhèu Yahudi sèra.<bt>Remember, ee! Those habitual decievers also believe in Yesus Kristus who died on the cross. But they want to force you-pl to get circumcised, because they are afraid of other Yahudi people that they will cause trouble for them, if they teach, that God also accepts people who do not follow the circumcision regulation. That's why they are trying to find face (=trying to please; 'suck up to') those Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="solo-mako = coax, suck up to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">solo-mako = coax, suck up to = rarange</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anagkazw: compel, make, force diwkw: persecute|i(12)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">anagkazw: compel, make, force diwkw: persecute<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>euproswpew: make a good showing, make a good impression LITERALLY: Those who want to make a good impression outwardly are trying to make you be circumcised. The only reason they do this is to avoid being persecuted for the cross of Christ.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Masi ka rèngu dhu suna le, te ngaa rèngu unu ra madhutu aa'i boe atora agama sèra. Rèngu d'èi ho miu madhutu suna, sèna ka j'aj'i dhèu rèngu. Dènge j'ara ne'e, partei ra ded'e padedha-dedha rèngu.<bt>Even though they are circumcised, nevertheless they themselves don't follow all the religious regulations. They want you-pl to follow circumcision to become their people. In that way, their party (=faction/group) will praise/exalt them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Not even those who are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Not even those who are circumcised obey the law, but they want you to be circumcised that they may boast about your flesh.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Te ngaa ja'a ne d'èi dhoka ded'e padedha-dedha Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus. Nèngu madhe ètu aj'u palolo-palèbha, sèna ka pamadhe aa'i bhabhelu-katub'a dhu dhèu ad'u-ue madhutu dad'èi rai-haha ne. Nèti èèna ka, ja'a pusi-pahae heka dènge dad'èi rai-haha. Aa dad'èi rai-haha ne èki heka ja'a.<bt>But as for me here, I only want to praise/exalt Yesus Kristus, our-inc Head. He died on the cross, to kill/put to death the evil things which humans do in following the world's will. That's why I am no longer concerned (=don't pay attention to, respond to) anymore about the world's will. And the things/desires/cares of this world do not bind me anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But may it never be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But may it never be that I should ever boast, except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, through whom the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Suna, do aad'o, ngaa-ngaa tao boe. Te ngaa dhu karisi, nuka èdhi abhu mamuri hiu nèti Lamatua.<bt>Circumcision or not, that's not important. But what is more important, is that we-inc receive new life from God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karisi = UNSs not know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">karisi = UNSs not know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akrobustia: uncircumcised LITERALLY: For circumcision is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">akrobustia: uncircumcised LITERALLY: For circumcision is not anything, nor uncircumcision, but a new creation.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ja'a manèngi sèna ka Ama Lamatua pad'elo sasue Na mi dhèu aa'i-aa'i dhu madhutu a'aj'a ja'a ne, ho rèngu mamuri padame, aa pad'elo rasa kasia èci dènge èci. Te rèngu j'aj'i le suku dhu hiu nèti Ama Lamatua.<bt>I request that God shows His love to all people who follow this teaching of mine, so that they may live in mutually peaceful relationships, and show mercy to each other. Cuz (elaboration) they have become God's new nation/tribe. [Follows NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sèna ka miu mamuri padame èci"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">sèna ka miu mamuri padame èci dènge èci.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eirene: peace eleos: mercy, pity|i(16) (16)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">eirene: peace eleos: mercy, pity<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>kanwn: rule stoixew: be in line with, follow this rule, live by this principle<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: As many as live according to this rule, peace to them and mercy, and upon the Israel of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ja'a peka mola-mola kèna, na, ja'a d'èi sèna ka dhèu sèku ia ka ja'a dènge lii langu suna ne. Te ètu ngi'u ja'a ne dènge tadha nu'a era, lula ja'a sab'a hia Yesus Kristus.<bt>To be honest, I don't want anyone to test/bother/disturb me any more over this matter/issue/ dispute. Cuz (elaboration) my body already has the sign of wounds (=scars), because I serve Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hisu = old scar (from disease)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z">hisu = old scar (from disease) ; hisu bai = bisul (lit. luka bangka) ; nu'a = luka, wound (new, fresh, wet, dry, old) from cut, accident, operation, or fight ; nu'a hiu = fresh or wet wound, cut ; tadha nu'a ~ bekas nu'a = scar (like my knee)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Finally, let no man trouble"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Finally, let no man trouble me, for I carry on my body the marks of the Lord Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />A'ari aa'i-aa'i! Ja'a manèngi sèna ka Kètu èdhi, Yesus Kristus, pad'elo d'ara hua iia Na asa miu aa'i-aa'i mi.<bt>Siblings! I request that Yesus Kristus, our-inc Head, show His goodness/grace/ generosity/kindness to all of you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The grace of our Lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-05 01:52:26Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirits, brothers. Amen!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">D'ai sange ne'e ka.<bt>That's it!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lii maho'o nèti ja'a,<bt>Greetings from me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Paulus<bt>Paulus</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>